1
00:00:06,999 --> 00:00:09,592
[12 years before this...]

2
00:00:09,592 --> 00:00:11,813
[June 2014, restaurant]
I'll fill you in on where we're headed.

3
00:00:11,813 --> 00:00:12,453
I'm so curious.

4
00:00:12,453 --> 00:00:13,693
Here are your tickets.

5
00:00:13,693 --> 00:00:15,860
- Just check in on your own.
- What's today's date?

6
00:00:15,860 --> 00:00:17,976
- It's today.
- Exactly.

7
00:00:19,645 --> 00:00:23,516
[Peru: snatched right off the bat]

8
00:00:23,516 --> 00:00:25,660
[July 2014, studio]

9
00:00:25,660 --> 00:00:28,092
Guys, you just need to head out.

10
00:00:28,092 --> 00:00:29,513
Wait, now? Like right this second?

11
00:00:29,513 --> 00:00:31,693
[Laos: kidnapped under a promo shoot]
- It's already five, move it. - Hurry up!

12
00:00:31,693 --> 00:00:33,472
What is going on!

13
00:00:33,472 --> 00:00:35,862
Hold on, I'm leaving dressed like this?
For real?

14
00:00:35,862 --> 00:00:36,829
[Iceland: kidnapped in a tuxedo]

15
00:00:36,829 --> 00:00:38,560
But I'm literally dressed like this.

16
00:00:38,560 --> 00:00:39,499
On the plane, though.

17
00:00:39,499 --> 00:00:41,934
[January 2016, Phuket]
One, two, three!

18
00:00:41,934 --> 00:00:43,293
You can head out right now.

19
00:00:43,293 --> 00:00:45,538
[Africa: kidnapped during Reply 1988 trip]
Hold on, what do you mean right now?

20
00:00:45,538 --> 00:00:46,713
Just get in that car.

21
00:00:46,713 --> 00:00:48,789
Going right to the airport.

22
00:00:49,609 --> 00:00:53,460
[And ten years later...]

23
00:00:53,460 --> 00:00:55,414
[February 2026, motel]
Ugh, it's so cold.

24
00:00:55,414 --> 00:00:57,283
Yeah.

25
00:00:57,283 --> 00:00:58,885
Okay, I'm good to go.

26
00:00:58,885 --> 00:01:01,643
Hi, I'm Jung Yumi.

27
00:01:01,643 --> 00:01:02,860
[Park Seo Jun]
Wait, we do this standing up?

28
00:01:02,860 --> 00:01:05,090
Yeah, just stay standing there.

29
00:01:05,758 --> 00:01:09,495
[Choi Woo Shik]

30
00:01:09,495 --> 00:01:11,523
All we knew was

31
00:01:11,523 --> 00:01:14,498
Seo Jun, Yumi, and Woo Shik, together.

32
00:01:14,498 --> 00:01:16,202
- That was literally it.
- That's it.

33
00:01:16,202 --> 00:01:19,537
Nobody's telling us what's happening.

34
00:01:19,537 --> 00:01:22,041
I tried guessing every possibility.

35
00:01:22,041 --> 00:01:23,738
I had zero clue, honestly.

36
00:01:23,738 --> 00:01:26,245
They got me so good.

37
00:01:26,245 --> 00:01:28,281
I really didn't know.

38
00:01:28,281 --> 00:01:29,582
Not at all.

39
00:01:29,582 --> 00:01:31,132
Where does

40
00:01:31,132 --> 00:01:33,298
the scheming even start?

41
00:01:33,298 --> 00:01:36,522
Getting yanked out of a livestream was not

42
00:01:36,522 --> 00:01:37,918
even on my radar.

43
00:01:37,918 --> 00:01:40,193
I could not have predicted
the livestream thing...

44
00:01:40,193 --> 00:01:42,094
The livestream part...

45
00:01:44,196 --> 00:01:47,193
- Hold on, we're going now...
- What?

46
00:01:47,193 --> 00:01:49,326
[A nationwide group effort to kidnap live]
Wait, this was a setup?

47
00:01:49,326 --> 00:01:52,092
Looks like we're leaving right now.

48
00:01:52,092 --> 00:01:54,802
- What's happening?
- So many fans are watching.

49
00:01:54,802 --> 00:01:57,043
- What?
- Wait, this was a setup?

50
00:01:57,043 --> 00:01:58,077
[Coming up shortly]
What the... hang on.

51
00:01:58,077 --> 00:02:00,341
[Three weeks before the decoy live]
All these fans tuning in...

52
00:02:01,059 --> 00:02:04,175
The real plan is...

53
00:02:04,175 --> 00:02:06,662
to fool them into a humble little trip

54
00:02:06,662 --> 00:02:08,521
around Korea.

55
00:02:08,521 --> 00:02:09,293
Yeah.

56
00:02:09,293 --> 00:02:11,227
- So that's the real plan.
- Got it.

57
00:02:11,227 --> 00:02:14,226
Think you can manage an "I have no idea"?

58
00:02:14,226 --> 00:02:15,660
- Just...
- Absolutely.

59
00:02:15,660 --> 00:02:17,563
Then set it up like that, please.

60
00:02:17,563 --> 00:02:19,898
Yes, got it.

61
00:02:21,734 --> 00:02:23,536
[Standby for pre-meeting:
Feb 24, Tue, noon (Egg)]

62
00:02:23,536 --> 00:02:26,992
[The cast will think
it's a regular pre-meeting]

63
00:02:26,992 --> 00:02:30,576
[Everyone's been brought in on it]

64
00:02:30,576 --> 00:02:31,883
[Today's live: 12 to 2 PM]

65
00:02:31,883 --> 00:02:34,213
[The day before the decoy live]

66
00:02:34,213 --> 00:02:37,083
[Something gets posted on Channel Full Moon...]

67
00:02:37,083 --> 00:02:38,202
[One odd live squeezed
between IVE and Kim Dae Myung...]

68
00:02:38,202 --> 00:02:39,198
[Channel Full Moon Live]

69
00:02:39,198 --> 00:02:40,386
["Introducing Our Staff,
Writer Kim Dae Ju Edition"]

70
00:02:40,386 --> 00:02:41,320
[Yumi, Dae Ju, Seo Jun, Woo Shik]

71
00:02:41,320 --> 00:02:45,057
[Kim Dae Ju, who's been with them all along]

72
00:02:45,057 --> 00:02:47,293
[Using a decoy live
about Kim Dae Ju's 20th anniversary]

73
00:02:47,293 --> 00:02:50,026
[Congrats! Kim Dae Ju's
20th anniversary celebration live]

74
00:02:50,026 --> 00:02:52,865
[The goal: casually get them into the studio]
Give me 10 min to drag Park Seo Jun,

75
00:02:52,865 --> 00:02:54,126
Choi Woo Shik, and Jung Yumi down here.

76
00:02:54,126 --> 00:02:57,003
Can't you make it in five?

77
00:02:57,003 --> 00:02:59,538
[The day of the decoy pre-meeting]

78
00:03:00,139 --> 00:03:04,477
[Surprise cameras set up throughout HQ]

79
00:03:04,477 --> 00:03:07,213
[Even up to the 4th floor meeting room]

80
00:03:07,213 --> 00:03:09,715
[All set]

81
00:03:09,715 --> 00:03:11,117
[Egg HQ, parking lot]

82
00:03:11,117 --> 00:03:14,020
[30 minutes before standby]

83
00:03:14,020 --> 00:03:17,189
[A black car suddenly pulls in]

84
00:03:17,189 --> 00:03:19,073
Oh? Yumi's here already.

85
00:03:19,073 --> 00:03:21,661
She's way too early, what do we do?

86
00:03:21,661 --> 00:03:25,224
[Current time: 11:30 AM,
Yumi arrived 30 min early]

87
00:03:25,224 --> 00:03:26,660
- You can stay in the car for now.
- What?

88
00:03:26,660 --> 00:03:28,734
Stay in the car,
the others will be here at 11:50...

89
00:03:28,734 --> 00:03:31,504
- Is it okay if I wait in the car?
- Yeah.

90
00:03:31,504 --> 00:03:32,638
[Just steps away from Yumi right now...]

91
00:03:32,638 --> 00:03:35,992
[The live studio]

92
00:03:35,992 --> 00:03:38,626
[Prep for the decoy live is still going]
There's still time, don't worry.

93
00:03:38,626 --> 00:03:40,979
Yumi's already outside.

94
00:03:42,648 --> 00:03:46,185
[Another car that showed up too early]

95
00:03:46,185 --> 00:03:48,555
[Woo Shik also arrived early]

96
00:03:48,555 --> 00:03:49,519
Hey.

97
00:03:49,519 --> 00:03:50,793
Nice ride!

98
00:03:50,793 --> 00:03:52,678
- What's so great? They're all the same.
- Hey!

99
00:03:52,678 --> 00:03:56,026
What are you even doing this early?

100
00:03:56,026 --> 00:03:56,918
- Move over.
- Why?

101
00:03:56,918 --> 00:03:59,059
[Bickering within three seconds of meeting]
Move, I want to try the seat. Out.

102
00:03:59,059 --> 00:04:01,126
Hold on, did you bring a bagged lunch?

103
00:04:01,126 --> 00:04:02,835
A lunchbox.

104
00:04:02,835 --> 00:04:06,497
Are you going to school right now or what?

105
00:04:06,497 --> 00:04:07,538
Off to school, huh...

106
00:04:07,538 --> 00:04:08,918
[Dressed up: level 5]
Are you going to school?

107
00:04:08,918 --> 00:04:10,657
[Dressed up: level 1]
You're so overdressed.

108
00:04:10,657 --> 00:04:13,578
[As those two bicker over who dressed up more]
Seo Jun, please... just dress casually.

109
00:04:13,578 --> 00:04:15,726
Seo Jun's such a fashion guy.

110
00:04:15,726 --> 00:04:16,884
Come on...

111
00:04:16,884 --> 00:04:17,883
Please...

112
00:04:17,883 --> 00:04:20,483
[The studio door quietly slides shut]

113
00:04:20,483 --> 00:04:21,491
Door's closed, right?

114
00:04:21,491 --> 00:04:23,226
Yeah, the curtain's drawn.

115
00:04:23,226 --> 00:04:25,558
They're still down in the garage, yeah?

116
00:04:25,558 --> 00:04:28,694
Ugh, keeping up this act is so hard.

117
00:04:28,694 --> 00:04:30,696
[Takes a deep breath]

118
00:04:30,696 --> 00:04:33,393
So I know they're here,

119
00:04:33,393 --> 00:04:36,126
but I'm not supposed to know
they came to celebrate me, right?

120
00:04:36,126 --> 00:04:37,026
Right.

121
00:04:37,026 --> 00:04:40,963
[Helper 1, Helper 2, Helper 3]
[Helpers dispatched from Channel Full Moon]

122
00:04:40,963 --> 00:04:44,867
[Here's a brief overview of the day's schedule]

123
00:04:44,867 --> 00:04:47,102
Alright, we'll go live from here at 12.

124
00:04:47,102 --> 00:04:48,404
While we kick off the live,

125
00:04:48,404 --> 00:04:53,308
those three go upstairs
to the 4th floor for "prep."

126
00:04:53,308 --> 00:04:55,721
They're going to be like,
"Where's PD Na Young Seok?"

127
00:04:55,721 --> 00:04:59,481
Just tell them he's doing a quick live
downstairs for Dae Ju's 20th.

128
00:04:59,481 --> 00:05:01,894
[Stalling begins]
Just say he'll be right up.

129
00:05:01,894 --> 00:05:05,287
Yumi actually follows our livestream.

130
00:05:05,287 --> 00:05:07,133
She watches our streams all the time.

131
00:05:07,133 --> 00:05:09,168
She might totally click on it.

132
00:05:09,168 --> 00:05:11,419
[Keep her off her phone]
When someone texts me that

133
00:05:11,419 --> 00:05:13,472
Yumi's talking and off her phone,

134
00:05:13,472 --> 00:05:16,866
that's when I spill everything
in ten minutes flat,

135
00:05:16,866 --> 00:05:17,867
[Off to go grab the cast]
then go up.

136
00:05:17,867 --> 00:05:19,736
Then upstairs I'll be like,

137
00:05:19,736 --> 00:05:22,305
"Come to think of it,
you all have history with Dae Ju."

138
00:05:22,305 --> 00:05:22,951
[Pause for effect]

139
00:05:22,951 --> 00:05:25,040
How about we swing by and congratulate him?

140
00:05:26,142 --> 00:05:29,679
Too suspicious? Does it seem off?

141
00:05:29,679 --> 00:05:31,948
[Weird or not, doesn't matter]
It's not super suspicious or anything...

142
00:05:31,948 --> 00:05:34,450
[Seo Jun has arrived]

143
00:05:34,450 --> 00:05:36,953
[Current time: 11:50 AM]
Please.

144
00:05:36,953 --> 00:05:39,165
Oh? He's wearing jeans.

145
00:05:39,165 --> 00:05:40,256
[Dressed up: level 4]

146
00:05:40,256 --> 00:05:41,324
Hey there.

147
00:05:41,324 --> 00:05:43,826
Is Woo Shik here? Where?

148
00:05:44,527 --> 00:05:46,429
[Yumi and Woo Shik still in the car]
Get out, hurry up.

149
00:05:46,429 --> 00:05:47,497
- I can't get out.
- You can't get out?

150
00:05:47,497 --> 00:05:49,332
- I really can't.
- Why not?

151
00:05:49,332 --> 00:05:52,569
I'm dressed way too down for this.

152
00:05:52,569 --> 00:05:55,071
She looks like she packed for a field trip.

153
00:05:55,071 --> 00:05:57,473
- It's just...
- The slipper bag, casual...

154
00:05:57,473 --> 00:06:00,677
I was told casual. Just look at him.

155
00:06:00,677 --> 00:06:05,281
- What's with the slippers?
- Not slippers!

156
00:06:05,281 --> 00:06:07,450
[Questions about all the bags]

157
00:06:07,450 --> 00:06:11,054
[They were told just come as usual...]

158
00:06:11,054 --> 00:06:14,357
Feels like she got a different memo.

159
00:06:14,357 --> 00:06:16,593
- You're just as clueless.
- Me too.

160
00:06:16,593 --> 00:06:18,595
- We're all in the dark here.
- Seriously, no other top with you?

161
00:06:18,595 --> 00:06:20,463
- I brought a jacket, okay.
- You're acting like you know more.

162
00:06:20,463 --> 00:06:21,431
I don't...
[Livestream room]
[Strolling past casually]

163
00:06:22,317 --> 00:06:23,633
Hello?

164
00:06:23,633 --> 00:06:25,902
- Which floor?
- Go up to four.

165
00:06:25,902 --> 00:06:27,369
The 4th floor?

166
00:06:28,238 --> 00:06:29,606
[On edge at the slightest noise]

167
00:06:29,606 --> 00:06:32,175
Gosh, this is killing my nerves.

168
00:06:32,175 --> 00:06:33,343
Noon on the dot.

169
00:06:33,343 --> 00:06:34,844
Let's do this! Let's roll!

170
00:06:34,844 --> 00:06:35,879
We're live now...

171
00:06:35,879 --> 00:06:38,414
Oh, it started! Look at that!

172
00:06:38,414 --> 00:06:40,083
Three "Wow"s showed up!

173
00:06:40,083 --> 00:06:42,552
[People start flooding in live]
Hey! Welcome, welcome!

174
00:06:42,552 --> 00:06:45,154
Happy 20th writing anniversary!

175
00:06:45,154 --> 00:06:46,923
Thanks so much!

176
00:06:46,923 --> 00:06:48,258
[Opening up with the decoy stream]

177
00:06:48,258 --> 00:06:51,160
Send some congrats, everyone!

178
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:54,597
[4F: fake meeting]
[1F: live studio]

179
00:06:54,597 --> 00:06:56,332
[All three made it to the 4th floor]

180
00:06:56,332 --> 00:06:58,868
Hey! Oh, long time no see!

181
00:06:58,868 --> 00:07:00,136
Oh, what's going on?

182
00:07:00,136 --> 00:07:01,571
Hello.

183
00:07:01,571 --> 00:07:03,139
- Hold on...
- Do you have other plans?

184
00:07:03,139 --> 00:07:04,674
No...

185
00:07:04,674 --> 00:07:06,743
I'm the only one with a wrong memo.

186
00:07:06,743 --> 00:07:10,222
She's literally on a school day vibe.

187
00:07:10,222 --> 00:07:13,249
That's not it, they said come casual!

188
00:07:13,249 --> 00:07:16,307
Even casual...

189
00:07:16,307 --> 00:07:18,321
after years on TV...

190
00:07:18,321 --> 00:07:20,490
At least look decent for the opening!

191
00:07:20,490 --> 00:07:21,858
- At least I wore makeup.
- What?

192
00:07:21,858 --> 00:07:24,360
- I'm wearing makeup.
- Of course you are!

193
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:26,329
When did you ever? Since when, huh?

194
00:07:26,329 --> 00:07:30,833
Pull up his first "Summer Vacation" clip.

195
00:07:30,833 --> 00:07:32,001
[His first "Summer Vacation" look...]

196
00:07:32,001 --> 00:07:34,003
- Back on "Summer Vacation"...
- First appearance.

197
00:07:34,003 --> 00:07:35,204
[Footage courtesy of CJ ENM]

198
00:07:35,204 --> 00:07:37,807
- What?
- I look so...

199
00:07:37,807 --> 00:07:39,842
I look so sloppy...

200
00:07:39,842 --> 00:07:41,954
- What's wrong?
- Huh?

201
00:07:41,954 --> 00:07:43,746
You showed up in a cotton tee from home.

202
00:07:43,746 --> 00:07:44,547
[Tables have turned]

203
00:07:44,547 --> 00:07:46,749
My mom gave me so much grief over that.

204
00:07:46,749 --> 00:07:49,752
Where's our captain at?

205
00:07:49,752 --> 00:07:50,753
- He's doing a live right now.
- He'll be up soon.

206
00:07:50,753 --> 00:07:53,256
- He'll be coming up shortly.
- It's Kim Dae Ju's 20th year today.

207
00:07:53,256 --> 00:07:55,792
He'll be coming up shortly.

208
00:07:55,792 --> 00:07:58,428
- It's already been 20 years.
- They're doing the live early today?

209
00:07:58,428 --> 00:08:00,530
[Oh right, she's the subscriber]

210
00:08:00,530 --> 00:08:03,967
[Suspicion creeps into the trio...]

211
00:08:03,967 --> 00:08:05,435
[One hour ago]

212
00:08:05,435 --> 00:08:08,104
Man, those ten minutes are nerve-racking.

213
00:08:08,104 --> 00:08:09,682
- That ten minutes is the worst part.
- Right.

214
00:08:09,682 --> 00:08:13,476
I'm such a terrible liar, so...

215
00:08:13,476 --> 00:08:14,844
I'm so nervous right now.

216
00:08:14,844 --> 00:08:18,348
[Staff shaking with nerves before it began]

217
00:08:18,348 --> 00:08:20,416
- He's doing a livestream first.
- He said he'll be on live first.

218
00:08:20,416 --> 00:08:22,694
Who even tunes into a live right now?

219
00:08:22,694 --> 00:08:24,287
What?

220
00:08:24,287 --> 00:08:27,024
- Lunch break viewers are no joke.
- For sure.

221
00:08:27,024 --> 00:08:28,500
[Crisis averted thanks to Yumi]

222
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:30,169
The live just kicked off?

223
00:08:30,169 --> 00:08:31,759
It's only like a 10-minute thing.

224
00:08:31,759 --> 00:08:33,319
Oh, he'll be right up then.

225
00:08:33,319 --> 00:08:34,673
[What a relief...]
Yeah.

226
00:08:34,673 --> 00:08:35,999
- Congrats.
- Oh, thanks a lot.

227
00:08:35,999 --> 00:08:37,879
- Thank you.
- Isn't it gorgeous?

228
00:08:37,879 --> 00:08:39,778
20th anniversary, oh man.

229
00:08:39,778 --> 00:08:43,719
The congrats comments are flooding in.

230
00:08:43,719 --> 00:08:47,853
For real, staying at a job 20 years is...

231
00:08:47,853 --> 00:08:49,822
That's no small thing.

232
00:08:49,822 --> 00:08:53,525
Never switching careers for 20 whole years...

233
00:08:53,525 --> 00:08:55,199
I really only have ten minutes here.

234
00:08:55,199 --> 00:08:58,030
- There's a shoot being set up right now.
- Yeah, I heard about that.

235
00:08:58,030 --> 00:09:00,732
[Meanwhile, still hanging on the 4th floor]
Wait, we're not doing a farm thing, right?

236
00:09:01,533 --> 00:09:02,679
I'm so curious I can't stand it.

237
00:09:02,679 --> 00:09:04,479
What the heck is this about?

238
00:09:04,479 --> 00:09:09,074
Why is it only us three from the show...

239
00:09:09,074 --> 00:09:11,076
Right? I'm low-key panicking over here.

240
00:09:11,076 --> 00:09:11,910
Me too.

241
00:09:11,910 --> 00:09:15,180
They're rolling the dice
big time this early on.

242
00:09:15,180 --> 00:09:19,585
Honestly, this lineup is peak snooze fest.

243
00:09:19,585 --> 00:09:21,820
There's going to be so much dead air...

244
00:09:21,820 --> 00:09:23,839
Hey, you okay? How are you holding up?

245
00:09:23,839 --> 00:09:25,146
- I'm running on a messed-up clock...
- Yeah, figures.

246
00:09:25,146 --> 00:09:27,092
[Seo Jun flew back from a US soccer game]
He literally flew in from the US yesterday.

247
00:09:27,092 --> 00:09:28,627
Bro, spill the details on that.

248
00:09:28,627 --> 00:09:29,595
- What do you want me to say?
- There were three goals, yeah?

249
00:09:29,595 --> 00:09:31,230
So how was it?

250
