00:19:23,254 --> 00:19:26,343
- take a trip around Korea...
- You're not asking AI, right?

502
00:19:26,343 --> 00:19:28,593
If they took off,

503
00:19:28,593 --> 00:19:30,395
when's the best time to leave?

504
00:19:30,395 --> 00:19:31,343
Right now?

505
00:19:31,343 --> 00:19:33,099
- Right now?
- "Let's go."

506
00:19:33,099 --> 00:19:34,663
- Now?
- Right now?

507
00:19:34,663 --> 00:19:37,328
- Right now.
- Right this instant.

508
00:19:38,426 --> 00:19:41,162
I guess that's the people's verdict.

509
00:19:41,162 --> 00:19:42,542
- Hey, Yumi.
- Yes?

510
00:19:42,542 --> 00:19:43,827
- Woo Shik.
- Yeah.

511
00:19:43,827 --> 00:19:45,176
- Seo Jun.
- Yeah.

512
00:19:45,176 --> 00:19:46,913
This is as if...

513
00:19:46,913 --> 00:19:51,164
- somebody planned all these answers...
- Why am I suddenly shaking?

514
00:19:52,560 --> 00:19:53,334
What's going on?

515
00:19:53,334 --> 00:19:54,987
- What?
- Maybe...

516
00:19:54,987 --> 00:19:56,421
Judging by all these comments...

517
00:19:56,421 --> 00:19:57,526
- What's going on?
- What?

518
00:19:57,526 --> 00:19:59,426
- What?
- Maybe...

519
00:19:59,426 --> 00:20:00,174
- You should probably head out...
- What?

520
00:20:00,174 --> 00:20:01,559
[Unplanned Trip: Limited Edition]
- What? - What?

521
00:20:01,559 --> 00:20:02,992
[Best wishes to Jung Yumi,
Park Seo Jun, Choi Woo Shik]

522
00:20:02,992 --> 00:20:04,493
This was all planned.

523
00:20:04,493 --> 00:20:05,726
- What?
- What?

524
00:20:05,726 --> 00:20:07,992
[A banner behind the banner?]
What?

525
00:20:07,992 --> 00:20:09,626
This was all planned.

526
00:20:09,626 --> 00:20:13,673
You should probably leave right now.

527
00:20:13,673 --> 00:20:15,806
- You should probably leave right now.
- What?

528
00:20:15,806 --> 00:20:18,259
[Hahaha]

529
00:20:18,259 --> 00:20:20,246
This was all planned.

530
00:20:20,246 --> 00:20:23,081
[Can't believe their own eyes]
You should probably leave right now.

531
00:20:23,081 --> 00:20:24,683
- What's happening?
- I mean,

532
00:20:24,683 --> 00:20:26,785
with all these people...

533
00:20:26,785 --> 00:20:28,693
- No way.
- This was all planned.

534
00:20:28,693 --> 00:20:29,959
Wait, hold on. What is this?

535
00:20:29,959 --> 00:20:32,857
All these subscribers...

536
00:20:32,857 --> 00:20:35,126
I felt totally blindsided, for real.

537
00:20:35,126 --> 00:20:37,075
"Wait, what's happening?"

538
00:20:37,075 --> 00:20:39,226
The moment that banner came off,

539
00:20:39,226 --> 00:20:42,556
within a fraction of a second...

540
00:20:42,556 --> 00:20:44,776
"How far back was this planned?"

541
00:20:44,776 --> 00:20:46,529
For real...

542
00:20:46,529 --> 00:20:48,640
I never thought a livestream would
turn into a kidnapping.

543
00:20:48,640 --> 00:20:50,159
Not even one percent of me saw it.

544
00:20:50,159 --> 00:20:52,426
I'm genuinely terrified.

545
00:20:52,426 --> 00:20:55,092
So many people, in perfect sync,

546
00:20:55,092 --> 00:20:56,781
- What even is this?
- carrying just 100,000 won,

547
00:20:56,781 --> 00:20:59,885
- are telling us to go right now.
- Hold on.

548
00:20:59,885 --> 00:21:03,026
- You all are such good actors.
- You're all way too good at this.

549
00:21:03,026 --> 00:21:06,091
- Seriously?
- Wait, is this all a lie too?

550
00:21:06,091 --> 00:21:08,530
So the whole anniversary was a lie?

551
00:21:08,530 --> 00:21:10,670
- It's the 22nd, not the 20th.
- Yeah, it's been 22 years.

552
00:21:10,670 --> 00:21:11,696
Are you serious?

553
00:21:11,696 --> 00:21:13,390
That was a lie too?

554
00:21:13,390 --> 00:21:15,100
- You planned this whole thing?
- Gosh.

555
00:21:15,100 --> 00:21:16,393
I'm so scared right now.

556
00:21:16,393 --> 00:21:18,103
No. I'm not going.

557
00:21:18,103 --> 00:21:19,443
I refuse. I'm not going.

558
00:21:19,443 --> 00:21:21,944
I had no idea you were this scary.

559
00:21:21,944 --> 00:21:24,165
I think you should leave right now.

560
00:21:24,165 --> 00:21:26,860
Seo Jun, read this out loud.

561
00:21:26,860 --> 00:21:28,907
I don't want to read it.

562
00:21:29,584 --> 00:21:31,350
Please, just read it for us.

563
00:21:31,350 --> 00:21:36,041
"Best of luck to Jung Yumi,
Park Seo Jun, and Choi Woo Shik?

564
00:21:36,041 --> 00:21:38,022
Wishing a safe trip and safe return.

565
00:21:38,022 --> 00:21:41,325
Unplanned Trip: Limited Edition."

566
00:21:41,926 --> 00:21:45,262
It literally says Limited Edition.

567
00:21:45,262 --> 00:21:48,593
Limited, as in things are capped.

568
00:21:48,593 --> 00:21:52,226
You all are about to have a restricted trip.

569
00:21:52,226 --> 00:21:54,582
For this one, we're going with

570
00:21:54,582 --> 00:21:56,622
Unplanned Trip: Limited Edition.

571
00:21:56,622 --> 00:21:58,343
We'll soak up every bit of this trip,

572
00:21:58,343 --> 00:22:00,059
be back in Seoul by Sunday,

573
00:22:00,059 --> 00:22:04,482
then hop on a livestream to fill you in.

574
00:22:05,150 --> 00:22:07,201
Exactly what you asked for,

575
00:22:07,201 --> 00:22:09,646
we'll do a local trip
on 100,000 won per person,

576
00:22:09,646 --> 00:22:10,822
so catch us again in seven days.

577
00:22:10,822 --> 00:22:12,082
Okay, see you all later!

578
00:22:12,082 --> 00:22:14,191
- See you!
- See you!

579
00:22:14,927 --> 00:22:15,894
This is insane.

580
00:22:15,894 --> 00:22:17,201
[Live ended]
This is insane.

581
00:22:17,201 --> 00:22:18,596
Man, every single one of you

582
00:22:18,596 --> 00:22:21,432
can really act, for real.

583
00:22:22,967 --> 00:22:24,002
That completely caught me off guard.

584
00:22:24,002 --> 00:22:25,537
Okay, so we're done with the live,

585
00:22:25,537 --> 00:22:27,762
but your part is only kicking off now.

586
00:22:27,762 --> 00:22:29,322
Have a seat, everyone.

587
00:22:29,322 --> 00:22:30,682
The pre-trip briefing happens right here.

588
00:22:30,682 --> 00:22:32,710
- In here? This is the spot?
- That's right.

589
00:22:32,710 --> 00:22:36,781
[At that moment, something massive comes in...]

590
00:22:38,183 --> 00:22:41,819
[Travel Restriction Notice]

591
00:22:43,514 --> 00:22:45,593
Wait, none of this is registering.

592
00:22:45,593 --> 00:22:49,275
The show's called "Unplanned Trip:
Limited Edition," yeah?

593
00:22:49,275 --> 00:22:51,729
- Limited. So restrictions apply here.
- Right.

594
00:22:51,729 --> 00:22:53,698
[They review the notice with five restrictions]
Time to break down each restriction.

595
00:22:53,698 --> 00:22:55,514
Woo Shik, start with the first one.

596
00:22:55,514 --> 00:22:58,575
Every day, you relocate to a new city.

597
00:22:58,575 --> 00:23:00,371
Seoul and Gyeonggi don't count.

598
00:23:00,371 --> 00:23:01,514
Every day?

599
00:23:01,514 --> 00:23:03,175
So we're moving somewhere new starting tonight?

600
00:23:03,175 --> 00:23:05,577
Once I'm done explaining,

601
00:23:05,577 --> 00:23:06,624
you'll be heading somewhere

602
00:23:06,624 --> 00:23:08,346
outside Seoul and Gyeonggi.

603
00:23:08,346 --> 00:23:10,034
Got it.

604
00:23:10,034 --> 00:23:12,375
So after we sleep,

605
00:23:12,375 --> 00:23:14,195
we leave for a different region in the morning?

606
00:23:14,195 --> 00:23:15,395
Morning, afternoon, evening, doesn't matter.

607
00:23:15,395 --> 00:23:17,055
- Anytime?
- Just make sure

608
00:23:17,055 --> 00:23:19,724
you're in a new region before the day's over.

609
00:23:19,724 --> 00:23:20,994
[Reality hits like clockwork]
Sure.

610
00:23:20,994 --> 00:23:22,861
Seo Jun, go ahead and read number two.

611
00:23:22,861 --> 00:23:25,730
Each person is capped at 100,000 won per day.

612
00:23:25,730 --> 00:23:27,065
No dipping into your own wallet.

613
00:23:27,065 --> 00:23:28,395
So it's 100,000 won per head...

614
00:23:28,395 --> 00:23:30,001
That barely covers transportation.

615
00:23:30,001 --> 00:23:32,259
- Does that include everything?
- Every last bit of it.

616
00:23:32,259 --> 00:23:34,173
Are you serious?

617
00:23:34,173 --> 00:23:35,793
So with 300,000 won,

618
00:23:35,793 --> 00:23:38,160
getting around and finding a place to sleep
are the biggest expenses.

619
00:23:38,160 --> 00:23:39,280
What about food?

620
00:23:39,280 --> 00:23:40,280
And gas money?

621
00:23:40,280 --> 00:23:42,647
Sorry, but gas isn't something
you need to stress over.

622
00:23:42,647 --> 00:23:44,359
There's no car.

623
00:23:44,359 --> 00:23:46,217
So it's public transit then...

624
00:23:46,217 --> 00:23:48,019
We're taking public transit?

625
00:23:48,019 --> 00:23:49,320
Starting right now?

626
00:23:49,320 --> 00:23:51,139
You're leaving pretty soon.

627
00:23:51,139 --> 00:23:53,725
So we didn't want you stressing over it.

628
00:23:53,725 --> 00:23:55,959
- You had your cars, right?
- Yeah.

629
00:23:55,959 --> 00:23:58,620
While you were doing the live,
we already sent them off.

630
00:23:58,620 --> 00:24:00,609
So there's nothing left to think about.

631
00:24:00,609 --> 00:24:03,468
So each of you gets 100,000 won

632
00:24:03,468 --> 00:24:07,338
to cover transit, a place to sleep, meals,

633
00:24:07,338 --> 00:24:09,290
socks for Woo Shik tomorrow,

634
00:24:09,290 --> 00:24:11,175
fresh underwear for Seo Jun...

635
00:24:11,175 --> 00:24:13,310
Wait, what does that mean?
Hold on, I'm not following.

636
00:24:13,310 --> 00:24:14,670
- What are you saying?
- Look, the thing is...

637
00:24:14,670 --> 00:24:16,526
Because you're leaving this instant,

638
00:24:16,526 --> 00:24:18,090
Unplanned Trip has always been

639
00:24:18,090 --> 00:24:20,418
- about taking off with nothing...
- Except we're not exactly young anymore.

640
00:24:20,418 --> 00:24:21,486
[At heart, though...]

641
00:24:21,486 --> 00:24:25,027
So "sent them off" means they drove away?

642
00:24:25,027 --> 00:24:26,288
- The cars?
- Right.

643
00:24:26,288 --> 00:24:27,667
They're already gone.

644
00:24:27,667 --> 00:24:30,728
We asked the managers to go

645
00:24:30,728 --> 00:24:34,298
somewhere you would never track down.

646
00:24:35,900 --> 00:24:38,359
- It'll work out somehow.
- Alright.

647
00:24:38,359 --> 00:24:40,628
Okay, Yumi, let's hear number three.

648
00:24:40,628 --> 00:24:43,141
Phone use is restricted during the trip.

649
00:24:43,141 --> 00:24:46,648
You do get one chance to use it per day,
but only at the accommodation.

650
00:24:46,648 --> 00:24:48,880
So it's a chance that's being granted.

651
00:24:48,880 --> 00:24:50,762
- Right.
- Not a guarantee, just an opportunity.

652
00:24:50,762 --> 00:24:53,785
Unplanned Trip: Limited Edition is a trip

653
00:24:53,785 --> 00:24:56,087
where being together is enough,
even without phones

654
00:24:56,087 --> 00:24:59,242
and with barely any money.
Doesn't that sound nice?

655
00:24:59,242 --> 00:25:01,659
I'm Po-po over here.

656
00:25:01,659 --> 00:25:02,662
What's Po-po supposed to mean?

657
00:25:02,662 --> 00:25:04,302
It means 44.

658
00:25:05,263 --> 00:25:07,098
- That's 44 alright.
- Sure is.

659
00:25:07,098 --> 00:25:07,726
Po-po.

660
00:25:07,726 --> 00:25:09,942
Think of this as going back to your roots,

661
00:25:09,942 --> 00:25:11,736
- back to that original spirit.
- Right.

662
00:25:11,736 --> 00:25:13,539
It's just... the stamina part...

663
00:25:14,439 --> 00:25:15,849
Woo Shik, read number four.

664
00:25:15,849 --> 00:25:18,377
A daily morning benefit will be provided.

665
00:25:18,377 --> 00:25:19,410
- But...
- Benefit.

666
00:25:19,410 --> 00:25:20,374
What kind of benefit?

667
00:25:20,374 --> 00:25:22,534
A hundred thousand won a day,
relocating every day,

668
00:25:22,534 --> 00:25:24,073
no phone access...

669
00:25:24,073 --> 00:25:26,234
This could get pretty rough for you all.

670
00:25:26,234 --> 00:25:27,713
- Yeah.
- Just a little.

671
00:25:27,713 --> 00:25:30,159
So every morning,

672
00:25:30,159 --> 00:25:32,724
we'll be handing out a benefit
that takes care of one thing

673
00:25:32,724 --> 00:25:35,813
[Written on three slips, drawn at random]
that's been tough for you.

674
00:25:35,813 --> 00:25:38,193
But what it is

675
00:25:38,193 --> 00:25:39,797
[Benefits revealed next week]
and how you'll receive it,

676
00:25:39,797 --> 00:25:42,273
we'll fill you in on that when the time comes.

677
00:25:42,273 --> 00:25:43,693
That's giving me chills.

678
00:25:43,693 --> 00:25:45,159
What's wrong, Po-po?

679
00:25:45,159 --> 00:25:48,059
I really wish this were a dream.

680
00:25:48,059 --> 00:25:49,607
If only it were...

681
00:25:49,607 --> 00:25:52,626
[And the fifth and final restriction]
Come back here on March 1,

682
00:25:52,626 --> 00:25:56,414
start the live,
and the trip officially wraps up.

683
00:25:56,414 --> 00:25:58,077
Never thought I'd actually be doing this.

684
00:25:58,077 --> 00:26:00,393
I know, I never saw myself
on Unplanned Trip either.

685
00:26:00,393 --> 00:26:03,141
Figured I'd just be stuck doing dishes forever.

686
00:26:04,789 --> 00:26:06,536
So where are we headed?

687
00:26:06,536 --> 00:26:08,926
Domestic travel is coming up a lot.

688
00:26:08,926 --> 00:26:11,695
[Relocating every day]

689
00:26:12,330 --> 00:26:15,066
[Across this vast country of South Korea]

690
00:26:15,066 --> 00:26:16,403
[Hit every spot with fresh air and clean water]
This place is gorgeous.

691
00:26:16,403 --> 00:26:18,542
- Oh, what is this place?
- Gosh.

692
00:26:18,542 --> 00:26:20,203
At least we did make it to the ocean.

693
00:26:20,203 --> 00:26:22,486
[Expect to be running every day...]
I've never done anything like this.

694
00:26:24,827 --> 00:26:26,423
You know...

695
00:26:26,423 --> 00:26:29,002
[Expect to have basically nothing]
There's still Spam here...

696
00:26:29,002 --> 00:26:30,181
- Thank you.
- They don't accept cash.

697
00:26:30,181 --> 00:26:31,159
You have to use the machine.

698
00:26:31,159 --> 00:26:32,852
Looks like there's no blanket.

699
00:26:32,852 --> 00:26:35,363
Adding a car rental will leave us with nothing.

700
00:26:35,363 --> 00:26:38,502
At least we'll be able to afford underwear.

701
00:26:38,502 --> 00:26:39,823
I really need a cup of coffee.

702
00:26:39,823 --> 00:26:41,342
I'm exhausted right now.

703
00:26:41,342 --> 00:26:42,922
Let's grab one.

704
00:26:42,922 --> 00:26:44,361
What do you think?

705
00:26:46,335 --> 00:26:47,632
[Don't expect this to go smoothly]

706
00:26:47,632 --> 00:26:49,035
Nobody's saying anything.

707
00:26:49,035 --> 00:26:50,101
- Did it pass?
- No way.

708
00:26:50,101 --> 00:26:51,326
Is that the one?

709
00:26:51,326 --> 00:26:52,804
- Probably not.
- One just slipped away.

710
00:26:52,804 --> 00:26:53,905
[Like a bus that already left]

711
00:26:53,905 --> 00:26:56,140
We need to get off!

712
00:26:56,140 --> 00:26:57,159
[Like doors that could close any second]

713
00:26:57,159 --> 00:26:59,278
This one.

714
00:26:59,278 --> 00:27:01,179
Oh, no!

715
00:27:01,179 --> 00:27:02,893
[Like a swing that moved faster than expected]

716
00:27:02,893 --> 00:27:04,417
- Closed today.
- This place too?

717
00:27:04,417 --> 00:27:06,350
Let's try calling.

718
00:27:06,350 --> 00:27:07,607
[Like a cold "Closed" sign]

719
00:27:07,607 --> 00:27:11,388
One person died overnight.

720
00:27:11,388 --> 00:27:13,158
The deceased is...

721
00:27:14,525 --> 00:27:16,136
Starting from now...

722
00:27:16,136 --> 00:27:17,555
Not a word...

723
00:27:17,555 --> 00:27:19,613
Night has come around again.

724
00:27:19,613 --> 00:27:22,967
But having the money capped definitely

725
00:27:22,967 --> 00:27:25,181
forces us to do things differently than usual.

726
00:27:25,181 --> 00:27:27,393
There's something fresh about that.

727
00:27:27,393 --> 00:27:28,071
Yeah.

728
00:27:28,071 --> 00:27:30,232
It would've been a totally different experience
doing it solo.

729
00:27:30,232 --> 00:27:32,877
[Nothing is going according to plan]

730
00:27:32,877 --> 00:27:34,645
Oh, hold on a second.

731
00:27:34,645 --> 00:27:36,082
What do we do? Where are we even going?

732
00:27:36,082 --> 00:27:37,682
That's exactly what we need to nail down first.

733
00:27:37,682 --> 00:27:38,921
So...

734
00:27:38,921 --> 00:27:39,992
Actually, I have a question.

735
00:27:39,992 --> 00:27:42,861
So we're capped at 100,000 won, right?

736
00:27:42,861 --> 00:27:45,322
If we save some,
can we just roll it over to the next day?

737
00:27:45,322 --> 00:27:46,501
Of course.

738
00:27:46,501 --> 00:27:48,881
- That part's completely up to you.
- Think we can pull it off?

739
00:27:48,881 --> 00:27:50,328
Only one way to find out.

740
00:27:50,328 --> 00:27:54,126
By the last day,
Woo Shik's beard is going to be like...

741
00:27:54,126 --> 00:27:55,401
And then the live turns on.

742
00:27:55,401 --> 00:27:58,259
Like someone who just got back from Everest.

743
00:27:58,259 --> 00:28:00,241
Toured the whole country

744
00:28:00,241 --> 00:28:02,166
[Allowance and Looks: Inversely Proportional]
and just looking absolutely rough...

745
00:28:02,166 --> 00:28:04,901
So should we start
with the farthest spot first?

746
00:28:04,901 --> 00:28:08,249
Since we're already doing this,
somewhere we've never been sounds right.

747
00:28:08,249 --> 00:28:10,114
Here's my take on it.

748
00:28:10,114 --> 00:28:12,270
We hit the farthest point on day one.

749
00:28:12,270 --> 00:28:13,390
And then we work our way back?

750
00:28:13,390 --> 00:28:15,920
- Exactly.
- That could actually work.

751
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:17,660
So, Jeju Island?

752
00:28:17,660 --> 00:28:19,423
- Jeju Island?
- Yeah, Jeju.

753
00:28:19,423 --> 00:28:22,493
Then we're not eating anything today?

754
00:28:23,326 --> 00:28:24,662
We've got 300,000 won for the day.

755
00:28:24,662 --> 00:28:26,991
I skipped breakfast this morning.

756
00:28:26,991 --> 00:28:29,800
- It's 300,000 a day.
- We could just ask for gochujang on the plane.

757
00:28:29,800 --> 00:28:31,202
- But...
- Jeju's probably pushing it.

758
00:28:31,202 --> 00:28:32,226
Really?

759
00:28:32,226 --> 00:28:34,974
What's the farthest we can get on the KTX?

760
00:28:34,974 --> 00:28:37,241
Busan or Gwangju?

761
00:28:37,241 --> 00:28:38,959
Yumi, doesn't your family live in Busan?

762
00:28:38,959 --> 00:28:39,822
Oh right, they do.

763
00:28:39,822 --> 00:28:42,046
Let's swing by and say hi to your family.

764
00:28:42,046 --> 00:28:43,460
[I'll pass on that one]

765
00:28:43,460 --> 00:28:45,017
Then let's go to Daegu.

766
00:28:45,017 --> 00:28:46,881
Do you know anyone in Daegu?

767
00:28:46,881 --> 00:28:48,721
Not really.

768
00:28:48,721 --> 00:28:50,159
- Alright, let's hear everyone's thoughts.
- Let's decide quickly.

769
00:28:50,159 --> 00:28:52,925
- So are we going for the farthest spot?
- What time is it right now?

770
00:28:52,925 --> 00:28:54,905
Are we just going to inch our way around?

771
00:28:54,905 --> 00:28:57,560
Or do we go all the way to the end
and work from there?

772
00:28:57,560 --> 00:28:58,331
I mean...

773
00:28:58,331 --> 00:29:00,793
Bam, bam, bam, bam!

774
00:29:00,793 --> 00:29:03,334
[Going way up without any reason...]
Bam, bam, bam, bam!

775
00:29:03,334 --> 00:29:05,239
[Um... sis...]

776
00:29:05,239 --> 00:29:08,747
Sis, pretty sure that one
just landed in Pyongyang.

777
00:29:08,747 --> 00:29:11,426
[That's a no-go zone]
So it's bam, bam, bam, bam!

778
00:29:11,426 --> 00:29:13,193
- Oh, I get what you're saying now.
- Like this, right?

779
00:29:13,193 --> 00:29:15,146
- So you mean covering big distances at a time?
- Exactly.

780
00:29:15,146 --> 00:29:17,014
- Spread out.
- Hit Chungcheong,

781
00:29:17,014 --> 00:29:19,800
- then Jeolla, then Gyeongsang?
- Right.

782
00:29:19,800 --> 00:29:20,718
That could work too.

783
00:29:20,718 --> 00:29:23,827
- We should at least cross one off first.
- Yeah, cross one off.

784
00:29:23,827 --> 00:29:24,927
[The first destination has everyone
thinking hard...]

785
00:29:24,927 --> 00:29:26,092
So what do we do...

786
00:29:26,092 --> 00:29:27,558
[Sliding over]
Should we start with Chungcheong?

787
00:29:27,558 --> 00:29:29,793
[One person charging at the map
like he's in a trance...]

788
00:29:29,793 --> 00:29:31,796
- So we...
- Yeah.

789
00:29:31,796 --> 00:29:33,488
Let's head over for some Boryeong Gulbi.

790
00:29:33,488 --> 00:29:35,548
What's Boryeong Gulbi?

791
00:29:35,548 --> 00:29:38,159
It's Yeonggwang Gulbi.

792
00:29:38,159 --> 00:29:39,704
Boryeong Gulbi.

793
00:29:39,704 --> 00:29:41,909
[Boryeong is known for mud,
Yeonggwang for dried yellow corvina]

794
00:29:41,909 --> 00:29:44,668
Let's think about what we actually
want for dinner.

795
00:29:44,668 --> 00:29:45,709
So we're going just for that?

796
00:29:45,709 --> 00:29:47,378
- Let's go for it.
- Yeah, let's do it.

797
00:29:47,378 --> 00:29:48,146
Sure.

798
00:29:48,146 --> 00:29:50,359
- Alright then...
- Boryeong Gulbi.

799
00:29:50,359 --> 00:29:51,259
[It's Yeonggwang...]
Boryeong Gulbi.

800
00:29:51,259 --> 00:29:52,829
- Boryeong...
- Which gulbi are we even talking about?

801
00:29:52,829 --> 00:29:53,893
It's from Yeonggwang.

802
00:29:53,893 --> 00:29:55,953
Isn't there one that starts with "Bo?"

803
00:29:55,953 --> 00:29:57,955
- Bori Gulbi.
- Bori Gulbi.

804
00:29:57,955 --> 00:29:59,056
[Laughing fit]
Bori Gulbi.

805
00:29:59,056 --> 00:30:00,358
[Cringe meter rising]

806
00:30:00,358 --> 00:30:03,101
[Let's see now...]

807
00:30:03,101 --> 00:30:05,062
Let's just go to Yeonggwang.

808
00:30:05,062 --> 00:30:07,382
[Quickly steering toward South Jeolla]
Where's Yeonggwang? Right here.

809
00:30:07,382 --> 00:30:10,502
It takes forever by car though.

810
00:30:10,502 --> 00:30:13,202
I've been out there for a shoot
and it's deep in.

811
00:30:13,202 --> 00:30:14,338
So then...

812
00:30:14,338 --> 00:30:16,407
- Going there would be great, but...
- Right.

813
00:30:16,407 --> 00:30:18,662
Getting there in one shot today
might not be realistic.

814
00:30:18,662 --> 00:30:20,862
- Somewhere, though...
- Oh, the food there is incredible.

815
00:30:20,862 --> 00:30:23,341
Should we just throw something
at the map right here?

816
00:30:23,341 --> 00:30:25,162
- That works.
- Alright, let's go with that.

817
00:30:25,162 --> 00:30:26,217
Yeah, that's not a bad call.

818
00:30:26,217 --> 00:30:28,211
- So what if we did it this way?
- What do you mean?

819
00:30:28,211 --> 00:30:30,788
Woo Shik, close your eyes
and walk over from there.

820
00:30:30,788 --> 00:30:33,190
- Just stab it.
- No, you walk forward first.

821
00:30:33,190 --> 00:30:36,127
[Places mentioned so far]
[Jeju, Busan, Daegu, Gyeongju, Geoje...]

822
00:30:36,127 --> 00:30:38,293
[Too many places everyone wants to visit...]

823
00:30:38,293 --> 00:30:40,199
Are we throwing the cap?

824
00:30:40,199 --> 00:30:42,951
Then let's settle it with rock paper scissors.

825
00:30:42,951 --> 00:30:45,671
- Whoever loses does the throwing.
- Loser throws.

826
00:30:45,671 --> 00:30:47,304
- Rock paper scissors.
- Rock paper scissors.

827
00:30:47,938 --> 00:30:49,860
[Woo Shik instantly crowned
the star of the show]

828
00:30:49,860 --> 00:30:51,175
Come on, get it right.

829
00:30:51,175 --> 00:30:53,210
[Massive pressure]

830
00:30:53,210 --> 00:30:54,772
[The first destination rests entirely
in Woo Shik's hands!]

831
00:30:54,772 --> 00:30:58,049
We throw it to mark a spot?

832
00:30:58,049 --> 00:31:00,226
[Staggering]

833
00:31:00,226 --> 00:31:02,472
[Absolute tension]
Gosh.

834
00:31:02,472 --> 00:31:03,993
If it lands in Gyeonggi, we're starting over.

835
00:31:03,993 --> 00:31:05,589
That's the rule.

836
00:31:07,226 --> 00:31:08,366
Watch yourself.

837
00:31:08,366 --> 00:31:09,295
[I'm Choi Woo Shik...]
Just point him in the right direction.

838
00:31:09,295 --> 00:31:11,369
[Seven years in variety, he just knows]
You're drifting somewhere else.

839
00:31:11,369 --> 00:31:13,552
We're not heading to North Korea, right?

840
00:31:13,552 --> 00:31:14,801
You can stop now.

841
00:31:14,801 --> 00:31:16,760
[Right away]
Where am I?

842
00:31:16,760 --> 00:31:18,660
[Dizzy]
Just set the direction, that's all.

843
00:31:18,660 --> 00:31:20,304
Here it goes.

844
00:31:20,938 --> 00:31:22,773
[Total chaos]

845
00:31:22,773 --> 00:31:23,693
[Not there...]

846
00:31:23,693 --> 00:31:25,660
Again!

847
00:31:25,660 --> 00:31:27,293
[Second try]
Going for it.

848
00:31:27,293 --> 00:31:29,393
Not that spot...

849
00:31:29,393 --> 00:31:31,215
- Where are you even stabbing?
- One more time, this is the last one.

850
00:31:31,215 --> 00:31:32,992
[Deep ocean]
How are we supposed to go to the sea?

851
00:31:32,992 --> 00:31:34,318
Going.

852
00:31:34,318 --> 00:31:36,026
[Final for real this time]

853
00:31:36,026 --> 00:31:37,254
Here we go.

854
00:31:37,254 --> 00:31:38,526
[Please, can we just go already...]

855
00:31:38,526 --> 00:31:39,959
That's it.

856
00:31:39,959 --> 00:31:41,559
- Hey.
- That's it.

857
00:31:41,559 --> 00:31:43,136
- Where is it?
- Where?

858
00:31:43,136 --> 00:31:44,717
- That's pretty far out.
- Where even is this?

859
00:31:44,717 --> 00:31:46,597
- Gumi. Some mountain in Gumi.
- Gumi.

860
00:31:46,597 --> 00:31:47,477
[The mark landed on Gumi, North Gyeongsang]
Gumi!

861
00:31:47,477 --> 00:31:49,426
Some township!

862
00:31:49,426 --> 00:31:50,796
Might as well check it out.

863
00:31:50,796 --> 00:31:51,969
Alright, should we get things rolling?

864
00:31:51,969 --> 00:31:54,872
So let's say we head out in five minutes.

865
00:31:54,872 --> 00:31:56,316
Five minutes from now?

866
00:31:56,316 --> 00:31:58,409
But I'm freezing right now.

867
00:31:58,409 --> 00:31:59,741
[Completely thrown off]

868
00:31:59,741 --> 00:32:01,879
Phones get collected here in five minutes,

869
00:32:01,879 --> 00:32:03,114
and then we're off.

870
00:32:03,114 --> 00:32:05,426
- Sure.
- What about our bags?

871
00:32:05,426 --> 00:32:06,283
Bags?

872
00:32:06,283 --> 00:32:07,642
- If you brought it...
- If that's your own stuff...

873
00:32:07,642 --> 00:32:09,460
[Carry-on items only]
Seriously? Okay, nice.

874
00:32:09,460 --> 00:32:11,992
[Earlier, when they first arrived]
She looks like she packed for a field trip.

875
00:32:11,992 --> 00:32:13,725
- The slipper bag, casual...
- Well...

876
00:32:13,725 --> 00:32:15,542
[Yumi and Seo Jun arrived with backpacks]
I was told casual.

877
00:32:15,542 --> 00:32:17,959
[And Woo Shik, who had a blast teasing her...]
Just look at him.

878
00:32:17,959 --> 00:32:19,062
What did you bring, Seo Jun?

879
00:32:19,062 --> 00:32:21,641
Just the basics, you know.

880
00:32:21,641 --> 00:32:23,134
Wait, you packed essentials?

881
00:32:23,134 --> 00:32:25,610
[Essentials for a... pre-shoot?]
Just stuff for washing up and things like that.

882
00:32:25,610 --> 00:32:27,026
- Same here.
- Why did you pack those?

883
00:32:27,026 --> 00:32:29,426
I still have to shave, at the very least.

884
00:32:29,426 --> 00:32:31,391
You didn't even know
where you were going today.

885
00:32:31,391 --> 00:32:32,410
It was just a pre-shoot meeting.

886
00:32:32,410 --> 00:32:35,071
Still, even without knowing,
I figured something was up.

887
00:32:35,071 --> 00:32:35,891
You knew, didn't you, Seo Jun?

888
00:32:35,891 --> 00:32:37,091
- You knew, didn't you?
- Come on, you knew, right?

889
00:32:37,091 --> 00:32:38,151
No, I had absolutely no idea.

890
00:32:38,151 --> 00:32:40,211
- That's exactly why you only brought a bag.
- What?

891
00:32:40,211 --> 00:32:41,571
You showed up with just a backpack.

892
00:32:41,571 --> 00:32:44,211
I only packed the bare minimum, just in case.

893
00:32:44,211 --> 00:32:45,811
- Exactly.
- I literally just showed up with a backpack.

894
00:32:45,811 --> 00:32:48,493
- Did you have some kind of feeling?
- Just...

895
00:32:48,493 --> 00:32:49,391
You're lying!

896
00:32:49,391 --> 00:32:50,861
I was thinking something was going on.

897
00:32:50,861 --> 00:32:52,771
Have you been talking to Geon Jun?

898
00:32:52,771 --> 00:32:55,377
[Unfair]
I don't even have his number.

899
00:32:55,377 --> 00:32:57,368
At this point,

900
00:32:57,368 --> 00:33:00,337
I'd say this kind of thing counts
as experience in its own way.

901
00:33:00,337 --> 00:33:02,740
If this had been my first time
working with you all,

902
00:33:02,740 --> 00:33:07,386
I probably would've shown up
without a second thought.

903
00:33:07,386 --> 00:33:09,646
Usually

904
00:33:09,646 --> 00:33:12,094
there's at least some heads-up
about where we're going,

905
00:33:12,094 --> 00:33:13,951
but there was nothing this time.

906
00:33:13,951 --> 00:33:18,685
So I realized the only one
looking out for me was myself.

907
00:33:18,685 --> 00:33:21,694
It's basically like packing a first-aid kit.

908
00:33:21,694 --> 00:33:23,312
Thinking along those lines,

909
00:33:23,312 --> 00:33:26,764
I figured I'd at least pack this much,
even if it gets taken away.

910
00:33:26,764 --> 00:33:28,966
Might as well bring it along first.

911
00:33:28,966 --> 00:33:31,402
[Acting every bit like a variety veteran
two years ahead of Woo Shik]

912
00:33:31,402 --> 00:33:35,206
[Another senior with a sharp nose]
Since nobody was telling us what was happening,

913
00:33:35,206 --> 00:33:37,608
I'm kind of a pack-it-all type by nature,

914
00:33:37,608 --> 00:33:39,844
so I packed what I could,

915
00:33:39,844 --> 00:33:41,687
and there were things just lying around.

916
00:33:41,687 --> 00:33:44,348
I just threw those into the bag.

917
00:33:44,348 --> 00:33:46,786
[Really glad she's a pack-it-all type...]

918
00:33:46,786 --> 00:33:49,053
I'll give you a moment
to search on your phones.

919
00:33:49,053 --> 00:33:49,799
[Still need to look up
the route and how to get there]

920
00:33:49,799 --> 00:33:51,020
- Oh, searching?
- We're searching?

921
00:33:51,020 --> 00:33:52,490
- Let's be quick about it.
- Phones are getting collected in five...

922
00:33:52,490 --> 00:33:55,099
I need to run upstairs real quick.

923
00:33:55,099 --> 00:33:56,794
Your bags are upstairs, right?

924
00:33:56,794 --> 00:33:59,845
- Alright.
- Grab whatever you need right now.

925
00:34:01,198 --> 00:34:05,593
[Time is precious...
the trio splits up to divide and conquer]

926
00:34:05,593 --> 00:34:09,507
Wait, why are you doing this to me...

927
00:34:09,507 --> 00:34:12,009
[Suddenly feeling wronged]

928
00:34:12,009 --> 00:34:13,579
Is this right?

929
00:34:13,579 --> 00:34:15,079
Are you coming along with us, Director?

930
00:34:15,079 --> 00:34:15,539
[A nod]

931
00:34:15,539 --> 00:34:16,647
You knew about this?

932
00:34:16,647 --> 00:34:18,249
[Another nod]

933
00:34:18,249 --> 00:34:20,019
[The only three who didn't know...]

934
00:34:20,019 --> 00:34:22,452
I still have chills from it.

935
00:34:23,220 --> 00:34:24,233
What is this?

936
00:34:24,233 --> 00:34:25,959
How did they pull this off?

937
00:34:25,959 --> 00:34:27,694
What am I supposed to do with this?

938
00:34:27,694 --> 00:34:31,273
Hold on a second.
My clothes, okay, clothes are fine for now.

939
00:34:31,273 --> 00:34:34,098
Just a moment. Wait.

940
00:34:34,098 --> 00:34:37,059
[Just throwing on whatever's in sight]

941
00:34:37,059 --> 00:34:39,193
Thank goodness,
I've got one extra outfit in this bag.

942
00:34:39,193 --> 00:34:40,371
Right in here.

943
00:34:40,371 --> 00:34:42,306
[The pack-it-all type always wins...]

944
00:34:42,306 --> 00:34:45,242
[Meanwhile, the search team is diving
deep into the internet...]

945
00:34:45,242 --> 00:34:47,393
- Looks like we need the subway station.
- Right.

946
00:34:47,393 --> 00:34:49,182
I should write this down.

947
00:34:49,182 --> 00:34:50,473
Writing it down won't help.

948
00:34:50,473 --> 00:34:52,241
Oh, right.

949
00:34:53,250 --> 00:34:57,321
[Scrutinizing the map from every angle]

950
00:34:57,321 --> 00:34:59,493
- There's so much good food in Daegu.
- Totally.

951
00:34:59,493 --> 00:35:01,625
Makchang.

952
00:35:01,625 --> 00:35:02,803
Should we hit the market?

953
00:35:02,803 --> 00:35:04,059
- Oh, I'm completely on board.
- The market.

954
00:35:04,059 --> 00:35:06,096
Oh, Daegu Mungtigi!

955
00:35:06,864 --> 00:35:07,965
[Found it...]

956
00:35:07,965 --> 00:35:10,203
[A reason to go to Daegu...]

957
00:35:10,203 --> 00:35:12,862
[Dinner plans shifted, next stop, Daegu]
That settles it, Daegu Mungtigi is the plan.

958
00:35:12,862 --> 00:35:15,526
We sleep in Daegu tonight and move on tomorrow.

959
00:35:15,526 --> 00:35:17,841
[This is the beauty of a spontaneous trip]
Then we take the KTX

960
00:35:17,841 --> 00:35:19,076
and head to Daegu...

961
00:35:19,076 --> 00:35:20,844
Let's bring it up when Yumi gets back.

962
00:35:20,844 --> 00:35:23,213
Since we're taking the KTX either way,

963
00:35:23,213 --> 00:35:26,573
let's say we head to Daegu first,
closest to Gumi.

964
00:35:26,573 --> 00:35:28,652
Then I'll grab my stuff from my car.

965
00:35:28,652 --> 00:35:29,887
Your car isn't here anymore.

966
00:35:29,887 --> 00:35:32,215
- Wait, really?
- The car is seriously gone.

967
00:35:33,827 --> 00:35:35,226
- Because I really...
- Woo Shik, snap out of it!

968
00:35:35,226 --> 00:35:36,860
- You're stuck in those clothes all day.
- Woo Shik, wake up!

969
00:35:36,860 --> 00:35:38,693
- You're wearing that for the whole week.
- For the whole week.

970
00:35:38,693 --> 00:35:39,697
That's not what I...

971
00:35:39,697 --> 00:35:41,544
[That's actually correct]

972
00:35:41,544 --> 00:35:43,594
So I can actually take my backpack?

973
00:35:43,594 --> 00:35:44,860
Of course, your stuff is yours to bring.

974
00:35:44,860 --> 00:35:46,119
Sounds good.

975
00:35:46,119 --> 00:35:48,640
You had even the slightest feeling, didn't you?

976
00:35:48,640 --> 00:35:50,693
No, it wasn't really a feeling,

977
00:35:50,693 --> 00:35:52,600
but something was clearly going on here.

978
00:35:52,600 --> 00:35:54,345
Because nobody was telling us anything.

979
00:35:54,345 --> 00:35:56,526
This pretty much had to be some kind of ambush.

980
00:35:56,526 --> 00:35:59,526
[A 9-year pro with a nose for patterns]
So you still picked up on the vibe?

981
00:35:59,526 --> 00:36:02,606
Yeah. Because they weren't giving us anything.

982
00:36:03,554 --> 00:36:05,922
Hey, at least grab this much.

983
00:36:06,959 --> 00:36:09,827
Let's get coffee before we leave.

984
00:36:09,827 --> 00:36:11,660
We have to grab coffee on the way out.

985
00:36:11,660 --> 00:36:14,398
[Gulping it down]

986
00:36:14,398 --> 00:36:18,519
[Seo Jun layers up with his hoodie
for one last defense against the cold]

987
00:36:18,519 --> 00:36:19,992
Drink your coffee, Yumi.

988
00:36:19,992 --> 00:36:21,580
No, I'm skipping it.
I'll end up needing the bathroom.

989
00:36:21,580 --> 00:36:23,927
If you ask for coffee today...

990
00:36:23,927 --> 00:36:25,409
No, I'm not drinking coffee.

991
00:36:25,409 --> 00:36:27,011
[Busy keeping tabs on Yumi's coffee
on top of everything]

992
00:36:27,011 --> 00:36:30,581
[What is he up to now...]

993
00:36:30,581 --> 00:36:31,949
[Rummaging around]

994
00:36:31,949 --> 00:36:33,726
[Swiping a hallabong]

995
00:36:33,726 --> 00:36:35,493
- Look at this guy.
- Choi Woo Shik.

996
00:36:35,493 --> 00:36:38,226
[After the hallabong, now sneaking snacks too]

997
00:36:38,226 --> 00:36:39,393
[Stashing any food in sight]
Come on, stop it.

998
00:36:39,393 --> 00:36:42,180
Woo Shik, let's not sink that low.

999
00:36:42,180 --> 00:36:45,941
A bag of shrimp crackers isn't crossing a line.

1000
00:36:45,941 --> 00:36:48,226
Okay, I'll give you one minute,

1001
00:36:48,226 --> 00:36:50,801
since your parents might start worrying,

1002
00:36:50,801 --> 00:36:53,270
so make your calls
before we collect the phones.

1003
00:36:53,270 --> 00:36:55,305
Alright, one minute starts now.

1004
00:36:55,305 --> 00:36:58,092
I need to reach Mom, quick.

1005
00:36:58,092 --> 00:37:00,628
[To Mom]
I'm here

1006
00:37:00,628 --> 00:37:03,241
with the crew, so don't worry.

1007
00:37:03,241 --> 00:37:07,017
And I won't be in touch for a week.

1008
00:37:07,017 --> 00:37:10,523
[Everyone scrambling to make their last texts]

1009
00:37:10,523 --> 00:37:13,390
This has really gone sideways.

1010
00:37:13,390 --> 00:37:15,893
[This one's too busy eating fruit...]

1011
00:37:15,893 --> 00:37:17,227
[Gulping away]

1012
00:37:17,227 --> 00:37:19,117
[Storing it all in his mouth for now]

1013
00:37:19,117 --> 00:37:21,238
Okay, you guys made your calls?

1014
00:37:21,238 --> 00:37:21,838
Geon Jun.

1015
00:37:21,838 --> 00:37:24,197
[Handing over the phone]
Now, please hand over your phones to me.

1016
00:37:24,197 --> 00:37:26,577
Wait, so it actually works like this?

1017
00:37:26,577 --> 00:37:27,638
It's off.

1018
00:37:27,638 --> 00:37:28,806
Then I'll turn mine off too.

1019
00:37:28,806 --> 00:37:30,373
[Now, about this phone bag...]

1020
00:37:30,973 --> 00:37:32,301
[Bag TMI: 1. Secured with magnetic closure]

1021
00:37:32,301 --> 00:37:34,144
[2. Phone safety visible at all times
3. Which means you might really miss it]

1022
00:37:34,144 --> 00:37:36,180
[The production team will keep them safe]

1023
00:37:36,180 --> 00:37:38,293
And here it is, 100,000 won per person,

1024
00:37:38,293 --> 00:37:39,560
300,000 won total.

1025
00:37:39,560 --> 00:37:41,151
- 30 bills of 10,000 won each.
- Am I holding this?

1026
00:37:41,151 --> 00:37:42,217
Right.

1027
00:37:42,217 --> 00:37:45,293
Inside here, there's
the Travel Restriction Notice and a map.

1028
00:37:45,293 --> 00:37:46,477
Got it.

1029
00:37:46,477 --> 00:37:49,559
And you can film as you go.

1030
00:37:49,559 --> 00:37:52,362
Woo Shik's into that,
so it's an old analog camcorder.

1031
00:37:52,362 --> 00:37:54,872
That's fantastic.

1032
00:37:55,599 --> 00:37:58,535
[Introducing the trio's
three travel essentials]

1033
00:37:58,535 --> 00:38:01,271
[#1. Cash wallet, 100,000 won per person,
300,000 won total]

1034
00:38:01,271 --> 00:38:03,640
[#2. Notebook and map,
a smooth-writing notebook with a national map]

1035
00:38:03,640 --> 00:38:05,209
[The Travel Restriction Notice is
inside the notebook too]

1036
00:38:05,209 --> 00:38:07,144
[Just in case you forget...]

1037
00:38:07,144 --> 00:38:08,779
[#3. Camcorder, pure analog vibes!
Record your memories]

1038
00:38:08,779 --> 00:38:09,747
["I'll get a great shot for you!"]

1039
00:38:09,747 --> 00:38:12,422
[With their three-item kit in hand,
the trio...]

1040
00:38:12,422 --> 00:38:14,451
Let's start by checking the money first.

1041
00:38:14,451 --> 00:38:15,385
[That same wallet from earlier]

1042
00:38:15,385 --> 00:38:16,940
[Park Seo Jun / treasurer]
How much was it, something and ten thousand?

1043
00:38:16,940 --> 00:38:18,399
17,500 won.

1044
00:38:18,399 --> 00:38:20,057
Hand over the change.

1045
00:38:20,057 --> 00:38:21,960
[The thing Park the treasurer does most]

1046
00:38:21,960 --> 00:38:25,125
[Counting cash]
One, two, three, four, five.

1047
00:38:25,125 --> 00:38:27,393
Hold on, let me check this.

1048
00:38:27,393 --> 00:38:30,634
[Absolutely meticulous with money]
Six, seven, eight, nine, ten.

1049
00:38:30,634 --> 00:38:32,469
Count it one more time.

1050
00:38:33,771 --> 00:38:36,173
[And what Park the treasurer loves most...]

1051
00:38:36,173 --> 00:38:38,112
The cheapest option, please.

1052
00:38:38,112 --> 00:38:39,409
Do whatever you feel like, Yumi.

1053
00:38:39,409 --> 00:38:40,359
[What's the occasion?]

1054
00:38:40,359 --> 00:38:41,992
Just nothing too expensive.

1055
00:38:41,992 --> 00:38:44,713
- Apparently an Americano's 2,500 won.
- Let's move.

1056
00:38:44,713 --> 00:38:46,219
- Somewhere cheaper?
- Exactly.

1057
00:38:46,219 --> 00:38:47,117
That's the way to go.

1058
00:38:47,117 --> 00:38:48,285
[Keeping it cheap, heading straight there]

1059
00:38:48,285 --> 00:38:50,033
[Meanwhile, another bold soul takes the lead]
Just head to the building next door.

1060
00:38:50,033 --> 00:38:51,929
A different building? Which direction?

1061
00:38:51,929 --> 00:38:54,026
[Jung Yumi / public connector]
- Would it be okay to ask? - Ask what?

1062
00:38:54,026 --> 00:38:55,759
Should we just ask how to get there?

1063
00:38:55,759 --> 00:38:57,726
Could you let us know
when to get off for Yulpo?

1064
00:38:57,726 --> 00:38:59,596
Of course.

1065
00:38:59,596 --> 00:39:01,365
[Is anyone there?]

1066
00:39:01,365 --> 00:39:03,170
[Lost no more, the human GPS has arrived]
There's a direct bus if you go to the terminal.

1067
00:39:03,170 --> 00:39:04,509
Oh, for real?

1068
00:39:04,509 --> 00:39:06,870
[Making small talk]
It's been years? Oh my.

1069
00:39:06,870 --> 00:39:08,726
- Do you two know each other?
- No.

1070
00:39:08,726 --> 00:39:10,989
[From elders to kids]
She's from Daegu.

1071
00:39:10,989 --> 00:39:13,649
- You're lovely.
- Thank you.

1072
00:39:13,649 --> 00:39:15,146
I feel like I've seen you somewhere before.

1073
00:39:15,146 --> 00:39:17,593
- Have some.
- Oh, thank you so much.

1074
00:39:17,593 --> 00:39:18,515
Sweet potato.

1075
00:39:18,515 --> 00:39:20,159
[With Yumi around,
sweet potatoes appear out of nowhere...]

1076
00:39:20,159 --> 00:39:22,920
[This one picks up the camera at any moment...]

1077
00:39:22,920 --> 00:39:23,994
[Choi Woo Shik, camcorder director]

1078
00:39:23,994 --> 00:39:25,684
Oh, this is nice.

1079
00:39:25,684 --> 00:39:27,463
Hold on, MZ shot.

1080
00:39:27,463 --> 00:39:28,725
Okay.

1081
00:39:28,725 --> 00:39:31,493
[Po-po Sis and the Almost-Forties.mov]

1082
00:39:31,493 --> 00:39:33,564
Cross over, please.

1083
00:39:33,564 --> 00:39:36,683
[Director Choi's direction
turns everything into a film]

1084
00:39:36,683 --> 00:39:37,901
[Charisma]
Hold it.

1085
00:39:37,901 --> 00:39:40,103
[Woo Shik CAM]

1086
00:39:40,103 --> 00:39:41,593
[May be somewhat experimental,
viewer discretion advised]

1087
00:39:41,593 --> 00:39:43,640
Sit lower, lower, even lower.

1088
00:39:43,640 --> 00:39:45,293
[Three genuine friends, three different styles]

1089
00:39:45,293 --> 00:39:46,779
Alright, good.

1090
00:39:46,779 --> 00:39:48,846
- Should I take this off?
- Wait.

1091
00:39:48,846 --> 00:39:50,760
[Taking a taste]

1092
00:39:50,760 --> 00:39:51,849
Let's save it for the end.

1093
00:39:51,849 --> 00:39:54,827
[Just enjoying it]

1094
00:39:54,827 --> 00:39:57,014
- Oh, so it's here!
- Over there.

1095
00:39:57,014 --> 00:39:58,988
This is the spot.

1096
00:39:59,974 --> 00:40:02,892
Alright, we're heading out.

1097
00:40:03,894 --> 00:40:06,954
Let's go!

1098
00:40:06,954 --> 00:40:09,867
[The trip begins]
Wait, why am I the only one in a coat...

1099
00:40:09,867 --> 00:40:12,936
[Egg building, Seoul Station, Daegu]

1100
00:40:12,936 --> 00:40:16,010
[How exactly, still unknown]

1101
00:40:16,010 --> 00:40:18,678
[Current time: 1:25 pm]
We need to get to Seoul Station first.

1102
00:40:18,678 --> 00:40:20,310
- Isn't the closest station Hakdong?
- Sinsa!

1103
00:40:20,310 --> 00:40:22,059
Sinsa Station!

1104
00:40:22,059 --> 00:40:24,100
Is Sinsa actually closer?
Doesn't this way lead to Hakdong?

1105
00:40:24,100 --> 00:40:25,627
But we'd have to transfer.

1106
00:40:25,627 --> 00:40:26,750
[Obstacles right from the start]

1107
00:40:26,750 --> 00:40:28,688
- From Sinsa Station...
- I don't know the subway map...

1108
00:40:28,688 --> 00:40:29,953
So from Sinsa...

1109
00:40:29,953 --> 00:40:30,893
[No phone means no searching,
and it's frustrating]

1110
00:40:30,893 --> 00:40:33,023
Going off memory here...

1111
00:40:33,023 --> 00:40:37,594
[Near the Egg building,
there's Hakdong Station and Sinsa Station...]

1112
00:40:37,594 --> 00:40:38,896
[Line 3 Sinsa Station, Egg building,
Line 7 Hakdong Station]

1113
00:40:38,896 --> 00:40:42,799
[Sinsa Station 14 min away,
Hakdong Station four min away]

1114
00:40:42,799 --> 00:40:44,505
If we walk straight down...

1115
00:40:44,505 --> 00:40:45,602
[Hey!]

1116
00:40:45,602 --> 00:40:47,456
[Glare]
Should we head to Hakdong?

1117
00:40:47,456 --> 00:40:48,217
Go for it!

1118
00:40:48,217 --> 00:40:49,797
Hakdong is on Line 7, we'd have to go around.

1119
00:40:49,797 --> 00:40:51,074
You should come with us.

1120
00:40:51,074 --> 00:40:52,875
[Sharp cut-off]
No, I've got things to do.

1121
00:40:52,875 --> 00:40:54,344
[The traitor arrives, a 22-year veteran writer]
Director, oh wait, Writer,

1122
00:40:54,344 --> 00:40:57,357
what's the best way to get to Seoul Station?

1123
00:40:57,357 --> 00:40:58,977
- By bus?
- Seoul Station?

1124
00:40:58,977 --> 00:41:01,193
The bus takes a bit of a detour.

1125
00:41:01,193 --> 00:41:02,686
The closest station is Hakdong, right?

1126
00:41:02,686 --> 00:41:04,454
Is Hakdong better or Sinsa?

1127
00:41:04,454 --> 00:41:05,526
[Sensing the moment, firing off questions]

1128
00:41:05,526 --> 00:41:07,260
Hakdong is the closer one.

1129
00:41:07,260 --> 00:41:08,137
Oh, really?

1130
00:41:08,137 --> 00:41:09,960
- Hakdong's the better call.
- Alright.

1131
00:41:09,960 --> 00:41:12,156
- Let's head out.
- Are you filming, Woo Shik?

1132
00:41:12,156 --> 00:41:13,196
Yeah.

1133
00:41:13,196 --> 00:41:15,726
[Woo Shik CAM, even filming the traitor!]

1134
00:41:15,726 --> 00:41:17,159
Have a safe trip.

1135
00:41:17,159 --> 00:41:19,359
- We're off.
- Take care.

1136
00:41:19,359 --> 00:41:20,626
- Let's head out.
- Let's go.

1137
00:41:20,626 --> 00:41:22,973
- Straight this way for now?
- Yeah.

1138
00:41:22,973 --> 00:41:25,642
[And they're officially on their way]

1139
00:41:25,642 --> 00:41:26,810
Let me take your bag, Yumi.

1140
00:41:26,810 --> 00:41:27,774
No, I'm fine, really.

1141
00:41:27,774 --> 00:41:29,346
- Just hand it over.
- No, later.

1142
00:41:29,346 --> 00:41:30,094
Fine.

1143
00:41:30,094 --> 00:41:32,082
- Hand it over later then.
- Got it.

1144
00:41:32,082 --> 00:41:33,519
[A gentle lift]

1145
00:41:33,519 --> 00:41:35,433
What did you pack all this for, though?

1146
00:41:35,433 --> 00:41:37,259
It's just stuff I always carry around.

1147
00:41:37,259 --> 00:41:39,054
[Maximalist Girl vs. Minimalist Guy]
We should do a "What's in my bag" later.

1148
00:41:39,054 --> 00:41:40,733
What's in my bag!

1149
00:41:40,733 --> 00:41:42,249
Hakdong Station is right here.

1150
00:41:42,249 --> 00:41:43,889
- Then let's head to Isu.
- Hello there.

1151
00:41:43,889 --> 00:41:46,730
Please go watch Number One.

1152
00:41:46,730 --> 00:41:49,849
[Note: At the time, Number One
starring Woo Shik was playing in theaters]

1153
00:41:49,849 --> 00:41:51,610
Yes, hello. That's right.

1154
00:41:51,610 --> 00:41:53,010
We're the Number One crew.

1155
00:41:53,010 --> 00:41:55,238
[Shameless? Truly Number One...]
Number One...

1156
00:41:55,238 --> 00:41:57,107
- Number One.
- Number One.

1157
00:41:57,107 --> 00:41:58,810
- Have you seen it, Yumi?
- Of course I have.

1158
00:41:58,810 --> 00:42:01,721
- Did you catch it?
- Haven't seen it yet.

1159
00:42:01,721 --> 00:42:04,250
- We should check the subway map.
- What?

1160
00:42:04,250 --> 00:42:06,369
[Trying to figure out the exact route]
The subway map.

1161
00:42:06,369 --> 00:42:08,950
Go to Isu and transfer straight to Line 4.

1162
00:42:08,950 --> 00:42:11,206
Didn't we ride Line 4 back
when we were in school?

1163
00:42:11,206 --> 00:42:13,226
- Rode Line 4, yeah.
- Right, exactly.

1164
00:42:13,226 --> 00:42:15,292
We went to school together,
or were we even in the same year?

1165
00:42:15,292 --> 00:42:16,767
- Same school.
- Same school.

1166
00:42:16,767 --> 00:42:19,359
If we're in the same class, I'm forty-four too.

1167
00:42:19,359 --> 00:42:20,826
Po-po is off-limits.

1168
00:42:20,826 --> 00:42:23,033
Getting a single-use ticket.

1169
00:42:23,033 --> 00:42:25,599
[Ticket machine spotted]

1170
00:42:25,599 --> 00:42:27,587
A transit card? Oh, a single-use one?

1171
00:42:27,587 --> 00:42:30,046
- What is this?
- Seoul Station.

1172
00:42:30,046 --> 00:42:31,146
Line 1?

1173
00:42:31,146 --> 00:42:33,576
Wait, the only line I know is Line 4.

1174
00:42:34,166 --> 00:42:35,679
- Hold on.
- Let's just take the one we know.

1175
00:42:35,679 --> 00:42:36,839
[Wants to be certain since it's the first trip]

1176
00:42:36,839 --> 00:42:38,827
Is there a subway map nearby?

1177
00:42:38,827 --> 00:42:40,653
[Striding right over]

1178
00:42:40,653 --> 00:42:42,219
Excuse me.

1179
00:42:42,219 --> 00:42:44,493
When we're trying to get to Seoul Station,

1180
00:42:44,493 --> 00:42:47,674
is Line 1 faster or Line 4?

1181
00:42:47,674 --> 00:42:48,774
You're headed to Seoul Station?

1182
00:42:48,774 --> 00:42:50,059
- Go to Isu Station first,
- Isu Station.

1183
00:42:50,059 --> 00:42:52,234
- then transfer to Line 4.
- Isu Station, then Line 4.

1184
00:42:52,234 --> 00:42:53,597
Thank you so much.

1185
00:42:53,597 --> 00:42:54,870
[Subway route: Line 7 Hakdong]

1186
00:42:54,870 --> 00:42:56,157
[Transfer to Line 4 at Isu,
Exit at Seoul Station]

1187
00:42:56,157 --> 00:42:57,373
[Current location: Hakdong]

1188
00:42:57,373 --> 00:43:02,508
[11 stations total, transfer to Line 4 at Isu]

1189
00:43:02,508 --> 00:43:04,359
That comes out to 6,750 won.

1190
00:43:04,359 --> 00:43:05,460
Got it.

1191
00:43:05,460 --> 00:43:08,314
[Expense log, subway fare, -6,750 won,
balance: 293,250 won]

1192
00:43:08,314 --> 00:43:09,760
[Splitting up the hard-earned transit cards]

1193
00:43:09,760 --> 00:43:11,568
Don't throw these away.

1194
00:43:11,568 --> 00:43:13,650
So this is the way we need to go.

1195
00:43:13,650 --> 00:43:14,760
[Direction already confirmed in advance]

1196
00:43:14,760 --> 00:43:16,568
It's this way.

1197
00:43:16,568 --> 00:43:18,188
- Is this the right way?
- It is.

1198
00:43:18,188 --> 00:43:20,390
[Made it in without a hitch]

1199
00:43:20,390 --> 00:43:23,293
[The trio steps onto the platform]

1200
00:43:23,293 --> 00:43:25,562
[Seo Jun heads straight for the subway map]

1201
00:43:25,562 --> 00:43:27,964
It's only four stops.

1202
00:43:27,964 --> 00:43:30,333
[Let's see here...]

1203
00:43:30,333 --> 00:43:32,081
[Woo Shik CAM, full of feeling]

1204
00:43:32,081 --> 00:43:33,488
The shot looks great here.

1205
00:43:33,488 --> 00:43:35,104
Get one from here too.

1206
00:43:35,927 --> 00:43:38,809
[Woo Shik CAM,
a director who actually listens...]

1207
00:43:38,809 --> 00:43:41,611
[Filming reflections in the glass door...]
I look so tiny in this.

1208
00:43:41,611 --> 00:43:44,114
[Instant youth film, just like that]

1209
00:43:44,114 --> 00:43:47,017
[Okay, cut]

1210
00:43:47,017 --> 00:43:49,119
But seriously,

1211
00:43:49,119 --> 00:43:51,154
- nobody saw the banner reveal coming.
- Yeah.

1212
00:43:51,154 --> 00:43:53,526
That part caught me completely off guard.

1213
00:43:53,526 --> 00:43:55,827
[Still gives chills just thinking about it]
I seriously got chills back there.

1214
00:43:55,827 --> 00:43:58,862
You're going to look so cool
all the way to the end.

1215
00:43:58,862 --> 00:44:01,864
[Set to be Mr. Autumn vibes
through the very end...]

1216
00:44:02,532 --> 00:44:04,847
- This is the right one?
- It's the right one.

1217
00:44:04,847 --> 00:44:06,408
Hold on. Let's find a corner spot.

1218
00:44:06,408 --> 00:44:07,468
Over here.

1219
00:44:07,468 --> 00:44:09,973
Let's just get on first.

1220
00:44:09,973 --> 00:44:11,441
[The older two just boarding without a plan...]

1221
00:44:11,441 --> 00:44:13,393
There, right there.

1222
00:44:13,393 --> 00:44:15,679
A corner... any corner...

1223
00:44:15,679 --> 00:44:18,281
[The youngest,
lost while searching for a corner...]

1224
00:44:18,281 --> 00:44:19,249
[Stifling a laugh]

1225
00:44:19,249 --> 00:44:21,785
[Woo Shik spotted in a different car]

1226
00:44:21,785 --> 00:44:24,221
[Regrouped successfully]

1227
00:44:24,221 --> 00:44:26,893
[Awkward; Barely holding it together...]

1228
00:44:26,893 --> 00:44:31,261
Hello.

1229
00:44:31,261 --> 00:44:33,463
[Exchanging greetings with pleased passengers]

1230
00:44:33,463 --> 00:44:34,226
Number One!

1231
00:44:34,226 --> 00:44:35,665
The movie Number One!

1232
00:44:35,665 --> 00:44:36,900
[Barely holding it...]

1233
00:44:36,900 --> 00:44:38,338
[Cringe]

1234
00:44:38,338 --> 00:44:40,027
- I'm starving.
- Same, I'm starving.

1235
00:44:40,027 --> 00:44:42,507
- Should've eaten that tomato.
- Let's grab udon.

1236
00:44:42,507 --> 00:44:43,827
Udon sounds good.

1237
00:44:43,827 --> 00:44:45,408
It's pricey though...

1238
00:44:45,408 --> 00:44:46,468
It runs about 8,000 won.

1239
00:44:46,468 --> 00:44:48,027
Let's just hit a convenience store.

1240
00:44:48,027 --> 00:44:50,914
First let's book the train tickets,
check the time and if...

1241
00:44:50,914 --> 00:44:52,593
- If there's time left over.
- Yeah.

1242
00:44:52,593 --> 00:44:54,177
[Lunch plans hinging on the train schedule]
If it's tight, let's just buy something

1243
00:44:54,177 --> 00:44:55,126
and board.

1244
00:44:55,126 --> 00:44:57,454
[Nodding... hard to argue with that...]

1245
00:44:57,454 --> 00:44:59,626
This stop is Isu Station.

1246
00:44:59,626 --> 00:45:02,459
[Pulling into Isu, the transfer station]

1247
00:45:02,459 --> 00:45:03,860
[Gathering things]

1248
00:45:03,860 --> 00:45:05,028
Watch your step.

1249
00:45:05,028 --> 00:45:06,663
[Director Choi scrambling to film something]

1250
00:45:06,663 --> 00:45:08,131
[Woo Shik CAM, Isu, doors opening on the right]

1251
00:45:08,131 --> 00:45:10,534
[First transfer station insert shot...
can't miss this...]

1252
00:45:10,534 --> 00:45:14,037
[Mission complete, exiting at Isu Station]

1253
00:45:14,037 --> 00:45:16,757
[Even getting the transfer sign on camera]

1254
00:45:16,757 --> 00:45:18,997
Right, I used to get off at this exact end.

1255
00:45:18,997 --> 00:45:21,490
[This route was Yumi's commute during college]
Back when I was in school.

1256
00:45:21,490 --> 00:45:23,480
It's a bit of a walk, though.

1257
00:45:23,480 --> 00:45:26,316
[Just follow me, I know Line 4 well]

1258
00:45:26,316 --> 00:45:30,086
[Walking a nostalgic path
for the first time in a while]

1259
00:45:30,086 --> 00:45:33,455
[Even the long transfer corridor
feels fun walking together...]

1260
00:45:33,455 --> 00:45:34,950
Wait, what's this?

1261
00:45:34,950 --> 00:45:35,811
Over here...

1262
00:45:35,811 --> 00:45:37,378
- No.
- No, don't spend anything right now.

1263
00:45:37,378 --> 00:45:38,693
[Cosmetic shopping: DENIED]
Buying anything right now is off the table.

1264
00:45:38,693 --> 00:45:40,864
Don't let it pull you in.

1265
00:45:40,864 --> 00:45:43,527
[Thankfully resisting temptation
and reaching the platform]

1266
00:45:43,527 --> 00:45:45,428
This honestly feels like being 20 again.

1267
00:45:45,428 --> 00:45:46,548
- 20 years old?
- Yeah.

1268
00:45:46,548 --> 00:45:49,573
[Memories bubbling up]
I rode this all the time back at 20.

1269
00:45:49,573 --> 00:45:52,776
[Line 4 arrives, carrying Yumi's memories]

1270
00:45:52,776 --> 00:45:55,959
[Transfer wrapped up without a hitch]

1271
00:45:55,959 --> 00:45:59,493
Honestly, Number One has been so good lately.

1272
00:45:59,493 --> 00:46:02,321
It's really something
the whole family can enjoy.

1273
00:46:02,321 --> 00:46:03,420
Right.

1274
00:46:03,420 --> 00:46:05,733
[Number One promotion complete on Line 4 too]

1275
00:46:05,733 --> 00:46:07,324
- What is this?
- What is this? What's in there?

1276
00:46:07,324 --> 00:46:09,259
- What's that?
- No, this isn't.

1277
00:46:09,259 --> 00:46:10,493
[The younger ones curious about Yumi's bag]
These are personal items...

1278
00:46:10,493 --> 00:46:13,797
- All of this will do you good.
- Seriously?

1279
00:46:13,797 --> 00:46:16,299
- What's that?
- Want some candy?

1280
00:46:16,299 --> 00:46:18,268
[Face lighting up]

1281
00:46:18,268 --> 00:46:20,193
[See, "do you good" turned into candy...]
I need to save these for now.

1282
00:46:20,193 --> 00:46:22,290
Should've held back
from sharing at the shop earlier.

1283
00:46:22,290 --> 00:46:24,190
Handed out a whole handful back at the shop.

1284
00:46:24,190 --> 00:46:26,593
These are good.

1285
00:46:26,593 --> 00:46:27,444
I'd like to share, but...
[Put it away]

1286
00:46:28,049 --> 00:46:30,026
Those people over there are all in on it.

1287
00:46:30,026 --> 00:46:31,581
[To crew]
Sorry I can't share any with you.

1288
00:46:31,581 --> 00:46:33,850
[Sorry, but gotta get the sugar in]

1289
00:46:33,850 --> 00:46:35,518
[Now's the time]

1290
00:46:35,518 --> 00:46:36,720
[Woo Shik CAM]

1291
00:46:36,720 --> 00:46:39,637
[Instantly becoming a youth film lead...]

1292
00:46:39,637 --> 00:46:41,658
- With this we could just shoot a...
- Music video.

1293
00:46:41,658 --> 00:46:43,358
- Should we film something?
- Let's do it.

1294
00:46:43,358 --> 00:46:45,437
[Youth Film by Director Choi]
You're the director, let's make a film.

1295
00:46:45,437 --> 00:46:46,878
They said it was supposed to snow today.

1296
00:46:46,878 --> 00:46:49,004
- Really?
- It won't snow in Daegu.

1297
00:46:49,004 --> 00:46:50,467
It'd be nice if it did snow.

1298
00:46:50,467 --> 00:46:52,297
[After taking in the view outside]

1299
00:46:52,297 --> 00:46:54,337
This stop is Seoul Station.

1300
00:46:54,337 --> 00:46:56,042
Seoul Station.

1301
00:46:56,042 --> 00:46:58,508
[Seoul Station already]
Doors opening on the left.

1302
00:46:58,508 --> 00:47:01,511
[11 stops later, exiting at Seoul Station]

1303
00:47:01,511 --> 00:47:03,380
- The KTX is over here.
- Right.

1304
00:47:03,380 --> 00:47:05,582
[Signs clearly marked on the floor too]

1305
00:47:05,582 --> 00:47:08,651
[Woo Shik CAM, buzzing with excitement
on the way to the train]

1306
00:47:09,832 --> 00:47:10,992
- Looking exhausted already.
- I'm hungry.

1307
00:47:10,992 --> 00:47:12,560
Seriously starving.

1308
00:47:12,560 --> 00:47:14,226
- You're hungry too, right?
- Yeah.

1309
00:47:14,226 --> 00:47:16,226
There's more walking ahead.

1310
00:47:16,226 --> 00:47:18,895
[Round two of walking begins]

1311
00:47:18,895 --> 00:47:21,865
[Walking side by side, and then some more...]

1312
00:47:21,865 --> 00:47:23,066
[Hopping up the stairs]

1313
00:47:23,066 --> 00:47:26,736
[Huffing and puffing]

1314
00:47:26,736 --> 00:47:30,307
[Running, walking, catching their breath]

1315
00:47:30,307 --> 00:47:33,276
[Woo Shik CAM]
[The finish line is right there]

1316
00:47:33,276 --> 00:47:35,945
[One last stairway to climb]

1317
00:47:35,945 --> 00:47:38,564
- Yes.
- It's the 2:28 train.

1318
00:47:38,564 --> 00:47:39,565
- What time is it even?
- Daegu.

1319
00:47:39,565 --> 00:47:41,217
- Just go, forget the time.
- Let's move.

1320
00:47:41,217 --> 00:47:43,390
[The trio finally enters the station]

1321
00:47:43,390 --> 00:47:45,284
Those dumplings look incredible.

1322
00:47:45,284 --> 00:47:47,393
Looks so good.

1323
00:47:47,393 --> 00:47:49,225
5,500 won.

1324
00:47:49,225 --> 00:47:50,760
[The price is tempting...]

1325
00:47:50,760 --> 00:47:53,427
[But tickets come first!]

1326
00:47:53,427 --> 00:47:54,364
Seo Jun.

1327
00:47:54,364 --> 00:47:56,193
[Over here]

1328
00:47:56,193 --> 00:47:57,860
Found it.

1329
00:47:57,860 --> 00:48:00,770
- Please enter your trip details.
- Daegu.

1330
00:48:00,770 --> 00:48:02,372
There's Dongdaegu and there's Daegu.

1331
00:48:02,372 --> 00:48:03,717
Dongdaegu.

1332
00:48:03,717 --> 00:48:05,293
Because Dongdaegu is the main station...

1333
00:48:05,293 --> 00:48:07,944
- Dongdaegu...
- Dongdaegu.

1334
00:48:07,944 --> 00:48:09,159
- Search for trains.
- Right.

1335
00:48:09,159 --> 00:48:10,905
- Please select a train.
- There are so many.

1336
00:48:10,905 --> 00:48:12,125
The 2:33.

1337
00:48:12,125 --> 00:48:13,424
[14:58 Seoul to 16:52 Dongdaegu]
There's one at 3:00.

1338
00:48:13,424 --> 00:48:15,537
Should we take the 3 o'clock?

1339
00:48:15,537 --> 00:48:18,365
- Please select your payment method.
- Cash.

1340
00:48:18,365 --> 00:48:20,026
- Wait?
- Cash isn't an option.

1341
00:48:20,026 --> 00:48:21,024
Oh no.

1342
00:48:21,024 --> 00:48:23,093
[Cash payment not accepted]
Oh my.

1343
00:48:23,093 --> 00:48:25,762
[Cash nowhere to be found]

1344
00:48:25,762 --> 00:48:27,630
[The trio caught completely off guard...]

1345
00:48:27,630 --> 00:48:29,666
Let's get over there fast, over there.

1346
00:48:29,666 --> 00:48:30,700
[What Yumi meant by "over there"...]

1347
00:48:30,700 --> 00:48:32,469
Cash isn't working here.

1348
00:48:32,469 --> 00:48:35,605
[A staffed counter right next to the kiosk]

1349
00:48:35,605 --> 00:48:38,504
[Lining up at the counter for now]

1350
00:48:38,504 --> 00:48:40,042
Or maybe...

1351
00:48:41,578 --> 00:48:43,605
We could just ask that person over there.

1352
00:48:43,605 --> 00:48:44,914
Exactly.

1353
00:48:44,914 --> 00:48:46,660
[Already heading over]

1354
00:48:46,660 --> 00:48:48,545
Is everything here card only?

1355
00:48:48,545 --> 00:48:49,600
Only cards work here.

1356
00:48:49,600 --> 00:48:51,165
- The cars?
- That's right.

1357
00:48:51,165 --> 00:48:53,423
- For cash...
- For cash, you'll need to go to the counter.

1358
00:48:53,423 --> 00:48:55,191
[A quick bow]
Understood.

1359
00:48:55,191 --> 00:48:57,460
[Hand signal sent to the one right across]

1360
00:48:57,460 --> 00:48:59,696
[Signal received]
Only this spot takes it.

1361
00:48:59,696 --> 00:49:01,764
[Their turn coming up]
Let's go.

1362
00:49:02,460 --> 00:49:03,992
- Hello.
- Hello.

1363
00:49:03,992 --> 00:49:06,855
We're heading to Dongdaegu.

1364
00:49:06,855 --> 00:49:08,775
- We only have cash.
- Oh, that's fine.

1365
00:49:08,775 --> 00:49:10,015
- Okay.
- How many in your group?

1366
00:49:10,015 --> 00:49:11,634
Three of us.

1367
00:49:11,634 --> 00:49:13,927
- The seats face each other, is that okay?
- That works for us.

1368
00:49:13,927 --> 00:49:15,241
That'll be 123,900 won.

1369
00:49:15,241 --> 00:49:17,683
- How much?
- 123,900 won.

1370
00:49:17,683 --> 00:49:18,927
[Stunned by the amount...]
Excuse me?

1371
00:49:18,927 --> 00:49:20,250
That's 130,000 won?

1372
00:49:20,250 --> 00:49:22,403
[The allowance nearly
cut in half in an instant...]

1373
00:49:22,403 --> 00:49:24,490
- So then this...
- Then give me just 20,000 won.

1374
00:49:24,490 --> 00:49:26,334
I'll go pick up some dumplings.

1375
00:49:26,334 --> 00:49:28,417
- Keep it under 20,000.
- Yeah, got it.

1376
00:49:28,417 --> 00:49:30,992
[She heads out to grab dumplings
before boarding]

1377
00:49:30,992 --> 00:49:32,598
- Head to the right.
- Row 245.

1378
00:49:32,598 --> 00:49:34,864
Thank you so much.

1379
00:49:34,864 --> 00:49:37,200
[Dongdaegu-bound tickets booked at 2:58]

1380
00:49:37,200 --> 00:49:39,536
[Huffing and puffing]

1381
00:49:39,536 --> 00:49:42,860
[Our girl Po-po has had quite
a lot of running to do today...]

1382
00:49:42,860 --> 00:49:46,075
One meat dumpling, please.

1383
00:49:46,075 --> 00:49:48,760
And two galbi dumplings.

1384
00:49:48,760 --> 00:49:51,150
[One dumpling per person, order placed]
One meat, two galbi, that's right?

1385
00:49:51,150 --> 00:49:52,460
Correct.

1386
00:49:52,460 --> 00:49:55,652
Sorry, could I also get just one water?

1387
00:49:55,652 --> 00:49:58,218
[Expense log, dumpling and water:
-17,500 won, balance: 151,850 won]

1388
00:49:58,218 --> 00:49:59,622
- It won't take long, right?
- About a minute.

1389
00:49:59,622 --> 00:50:00,790
Thank you.

1390
00:50:00,790 --> 00:50:04,027
[The younger crew with tickets
moving in to meet Yumi]

1391
00:50:04,027 --> 00:50:05,351
There she is!

1392
00:50:05,351 --> 00:50:07,670
[Regrouping after completing their missions]

1393
00:50:07,670 --> 00:50:08,765
Thank you!

1394
00:50:08,765 --> 00:50:10,933
[Amazing dumplings, ready in just one minute]

1395
00:50:10,933 --> 00:50:12,004
Let's go, let's go!

1396
00:50:12,004 --> 00:50:14,931
[Dumplings secured with time to spare!]

1397
00:50:14,931 --> 00:50:17,574
- Should we eat here too?
- Yeah.

1398
00:50:17,574 --> 00:50:19,309
Let's go up there.

1399
00:50:19,309 --> 00:50:22,212
[Striding up the stairs]

1400
00:50:22,212 --> 00:50:25,619
[Short on time, they settle for the stairs]

1401
00:50:25,619 --> 00:50:26,886
Ah, let's sit down for a bit.

1402
00:50:26,886 --> 00:50:30,653
[First time sitting down since they left]

1403
00:50:30,653 --> 00:50:32,555
Let's eat here real quick.

1404
00:50:32,555 --> 00:50:34,390
Did you get a lot?

1405
00:50:34,390 --> 00:50:36,059
- I got three.
- Oh.

1406
00:50:36,059 --> 00:50:37,727
One pork, two galbi.

1407
00:50:37,727 --> 00:50:39,095
Oh, I'll take galbi.

1408
00:50:39,095 --> 00:50:40,362
Yeah, that one's pork. This is galbi.

1409
00:50:40,362 --> 00:50:41,441
- Galbi?
- Galbi.

1410
00:50:41,441 --> 00:50:43,933
- What about you, Yumi?
- Let's share.

1411
00:50:43,933 --> 00:50:45,379
- Half and half?
- What are you getting? Up to you.

1412
00:50:45,379 --> 00:50:46,836
Oh, we can just share.

1413
00:50:46,836 --> 00:50:48,641
Hold this for now.

1414
00:50:49,606 --> 00:50:53,743
[Sweet Seo Jun is opening
the pickled radish for them]

1415
00:50:53,743 --> 00:50:56,646
[Neatly arranged]

1416
00:50:56,646 --> 00:50:59,449
- You got one bottle of water.
- You have it.

1417
00:50:59,449 --> 00:51:01,849
We're really pinching pennies,
getting just one bottle of water.

1418
00:51:01,849 --> 00:51:03,209
Sorry.

1419
00:51:03,209 --> 00:51:05,295
I won't drink.

1420
00:51:05,295 --> 00:51:07,182
Let's share it.

1421
00:51:07,182 --> 00:51:08,234
Thanks for the food.

1422
00:51:08,234 --> 00:51:11,294
[Finally taking a bite of
the legendary dumplings]

1423
00:51:11,294 --> 00:51:13,153
Wow, nice and warm.

1424
00:51:15,400 --> 00:51:18,704
[So good, they wake you right up]

1425
00:51:18,704 --> 00:51:21,820
[Dumpling trade]

1426
00:51:21,820 --> 00:51:23,025
Might try the pork too.

1427
00:51:23,025 --> 00:51:24,954
[Stuffing two dumplings in at once]

1428
00:51:24,954 --> 00:51:26,879
How much do we have left, seriously?

1429
00:51:26,879 --> 00:51:28,839
Let's eat first, then think.

1430
00:51:30,069 --> 00:51:33,259
[Let's worry about money after we eat...]

1431
00:51:33,259 --> 00:51:35,259
We're going to Daegu,
so let's have mungtigi today.

1432
00:51:35,259 --> 00:51:36,989
What's that?

1433
00:51:36,989 --> 00:51:40,256
- Mungtigi...
- It's kind of like... raw beef!

1434
00:51:40,256 --> 00:51:42,614
If you have it with soju,

1435
00:51:42,614 --> 00:51:44,527
you won't even get a hangover.

1436
00:51:44,527 --> 00:51:45,962
[Woo Shik's favorite pairing: mungtigi]

1437
00:51:45,962 --> 00:51:49,596
- We could also look for a classic local spot.
- Yeah.

1438
00:51:49,596 --> 00:51:51,556
- Somewhere cheap!
- Oh right, we don't have phones, huh?

1439
00:51:51,556 --> 00:51:52,701
[No phone to find a classic local spot]
Huh?

1440
00:51:52,701 --> 00:51:54,819
- We don't even have phones.
- Yeah.

1441
00:51:54,819 --> 00:51:56,086
Guess we'll look around.

1442
00:51:56,086 --> 00:51:58,325
We don't have phones,
so we can't look up good places.

1443
00:51:58,325 --> 00:52:00,709
We'll just ask around when we get there.

1444
00:52:00,709 --> 00:52:02,946
[Anyway, communication complete]

1445
00:52:04,309 --> 00:52:05,715
[Smooth and efficient]

1446
00:52:05,715 --> 00:52:07,614
[Gather the trash in one place]

1447
00:52:07,614 --> 00:52:11,022
[And clean up neatly]

1448
00:52:11,854 --> 00:52:14,490
Not bringing essentials is a big problem.

1449
00:52:14,490 --> 00:52:17,827
You two are fine.
I've still got to buy underwear...

1450
00:52:17,827 --> 00:52:19,332
- Just wear mine.
- And for a toothbrush...

1451
00:52:19,332 --> 00:52:21,592
- How would I wear that?
- I already washed it.

1452
00:52:21,592 --> 00:52:22,765
Come on.

1453
00:52:22,765 --> 00:52:25,517
Just buy one and keep washing and reusing it.

1454
00:52:25,517 --> 00:52:27,904
I need a razor and a toothbrush too...

1455
00:52:27,904 --> 00:52:29,205
You're gonna be expensive...

1456
00:52:29,205 --> 00:52:30,840
Just use the disposable ones at the motel.

1457
00:52:30,840 --> 00:52:32,446
- Use them.
- Ah...

1458
00:52:32,446 --> 00:52:34,751
- Yeah, just use them.
- I don't even have a charger.

1459
00:52:34,751 --> 00:52:38,493
- We don't need one, we don't even have phones.
- Oh, right. No phones.

1460
00:52:38,493 --> 00:52:41,569
Oh yeah. Then we don't need chargers.

1461
00:52:41,569 --> 00:52:44,376
Why did I even bring this without a phone?

1462
00:52:44,376 --> 00:52:46,656
[Peekaboo]

1463
00:52:46,656 --> 00:52:48,596
It's heavy, so just for a sec...

1464
00:52:48,596 --> 00:52:51,623
[Just a heavy, useless burden to come]

1465
00:52:51,623 --> 00:52:52,670
Do you have a mirror?

1466
00:52:52,670 --> 00:52:54,759
- Want one?
- Really?

1467
00:52:56,132 --> 00:52:57,333
- It's a cushion compact.
- Oh.

1468
00:52:57,333 --> 00:52:59,605
- Wait, I'll wipe it...
- Got any tissues? Nose ones?

1469
00:52:59,605 --> 00:53:01,218
- Wait a second.
- Just one for my nose.

1470
00:53:01,218 --> 00:53:04,317
No, this is the only one I've got.

1471
00:53:04,317 --> 00:53:06,689
- What's going on right now?
- A runny nose!

1472
00:53:06,689 --> 00:53:09,156
Just use the toilet paper over there.

1473
00:53:09,156 --> 00:53:10,335
There's no tissue.

1474
00:53:10,335 --> 00:53:13,549
Just use the bathroom tissue from now on.
We're out.

1475
00:53:13,549 --> 00:53:14,616
The train's here!

1476
00:53:14,616 --> 00:53:15,985
Oh, let's go.

1477
00:53:15,985 --> 00:53:17,790
- Four minutes left.
- Yeah.

1478
00:53:17,790 --> 00:53:18,897
Let's go!

1479
00:53:18,897 --> 00:53:20,683
[Heading to the train]

1480
00:53:20,683 --> 00:53:23,882
Hello! Please watch "Number One."
The movie "Number One."

1481
00:53:24,861 --> 00:53:29,181
["Number One" even on the platform]
It's a movie called "Number One."

1482
00:53:29,917 --> 00:53:32,472
[Boarding Car No. 13]

1483
00:53:32,472 --> 00:53:36,406
The movie "Number One..."

1484
00:53:36,406 --> 00:53:39,586
[Finally departing for the first destination]

1485
00:53:40,373 --> 00:53:42,976
[Fidgeting]

1486
00:53:46,844 --> 00:53:49,476
[The two actors adjusting the angle themselves]

1487
00:53:49,476 --> 00:53:51,310
That's the one.

1488
00:53:51,310 --> 00:53:52,836
It works, done.

1489
00:53:52,836 --> 00:53:55,191
[Yumi's cam ON]

1490
00:53:55,191 --> 00:53:57,664
- Huh? This way or that way?
- This way.

1491
00:53:57,664 --> 00:53:59,633
- This way?
- Yeah.

1492
00:53:59,633 --> 00:54:01,459
Is backward seating okay for you?

1493
00:54:01,459 --> 00:54:03,567
We can switch if it's uncomfortable.

1494
00:54:04,749 --> 00:54:08,621
[Now heading south]

1495
00:54:09,755 --> 00:54:11,702
Give me the cam.

1496
00:54:13,769 --> 00:54:16,062
[Camera duty switch for a moment]

1497
00:54:16,062 --> 00:54:18,347
Huh? You pressed it, right?

1498
00:54:18,347 --> 00:54:19,849
This feels like one of those...

1499
00:54:19,849 --> 00:54:24,670
You know, people usually die
filming stuff like this... in accidents.

1500
00:54:24,670 --> 00:54:28,739
In "Train to Busan," they're filming like this
before zombies appear.

1501
00:54:28,739 --> 00:54:31,812
So your last smiling face ends up on camera.

1502
00:54:31,812 --> 00:54:33,922
Hey, how fun is this going to be?

1503
00:54:33,922 --> 00:54:35,170
- I'm actually so excited.
- Yeah, right.

1504
00:54:35,170 --> 00:54:37,099
[S#1. A brief moment of happiness]

1505
00:54:37,099 --> 00:54:38,928
Next scene.

1506
00:54:38,928 --> 00:54:39,995
Zombies.

1507
00:54:39,995 --> 00:54:41,414
[S#2. Zombie appearance]

1508
00:54:41,414 --> 00:54:43,749
The camera falls, glitching on the ground.

1509
00:54:43,749 --> 00:54:45,229
[Director Yumi's experimental shot]

1510
00:54:45,229 --> 00:54:47,911
And there's a scream inside.

1511
00:54:48,575 --> 00:54:52,801
Yumi and I are not supposed
to ride the KTX together.

1512
00:54:53,679 --> 00:54:55,937
Zombies show up.

1513
00:54:55,937 --> 00:55:00,734
[Yumi and Woo Shik both starred
in the KTX-set film "Train to Busan"]

1514
00:55:00,734 --> 00:55:02,740
Right, right.

1515
00:55:03,514 --> 00:55:06,794
- Stay still for a second.
- The view outside...

1516
00:55:08,122 --> 00:55:11,022
[The view of Woo Shik]

1517
00:55:14,644 --> 00:55:15,811
Done!

1518
00:55:15,811 --> 00:55:18,810
[Director Yumi is satisfied]

1519
00:55:18,810 --> 00:55:21,468
[Woo Shik begins his turn as well]

1520
00:55:22,678 --> 00:55:24,058
[Peace sign]

1521
00:55:27,703 --> 00:55:29,447
[Intense gaze]

1522
00:55:32,522 --> 00:55:36,093
[S#3. Back to a happy moment]

1523
00:55:41,464 --> 00:55:43,053
And after this,

1524
00:55:44,090 --> 00:55:45,395
in the next scene...

1525
00:55:45,395 --> 00:55:47,942
[S#4. Zombies appear again]
Aah! Aah!

1526
00:55:47,942 --> 00:55:51,551
[They're reenacting "Train to Busan"]

1527
00:55:51,551 --> 00:55:53,488
You're exactly the same.

1528
00:55:53,488 --> 00:55:54,811
- What do you mean?
- Your face...

1529
00:55:54,811 --> 00:55:58,400
it's just like back then.

1530
00:55:58,400 --> 00:56:01,426
[No difference from "Train to Busan,"
10 years ago]

1531
00:56:04,387 --> 00:56:07,335
[With no phones, there's nothing to do]

1532
00:56:08,109 --> 00:56:10,492
[Rummaging]

1533
00:56:10,492 --> 00:56:12,161
[Ta-da]

1534
00:56:12,161 --> 00:56:14,694
- Jung Yumi's "What's in My Bag."
- Oh, let me have one.

1535
00:56:14,694 --> 00:56:16,699
Let's begin. No, we need to save it.

1536
00:56:16,699 --> 00:56:18,581
I have lenses.

1537
00:56:19,579 --> 00:56:21,771
- I almost bought lenses.
- I have sunscreen, too.

1538
00:56:21,771 --> 00:56:24,073
Oh, thank goodness!

1539
00:56:24,073 --> 00:56:26,425
- I have tone-up cream.
- Nice!

1540
00:56:26,425 --> 00:56:28,085
- Got it at the makeup shop earlier.
- Nice!

1541
00:56:28,085 --> 00:56:29,533
Whoa!

1542
00:56:29,533 --> 00:56:32,118
- I'll use some too.
- Yay, nice!

1543
00:56:32,118 --> 00:56:34,241
Yay... oh!

1544
00:56:34,241 --> 00:56:37,220
- Disposable skincare set.
- Nice!

1545
00:56:37,220 --> 00:56:41,008
I brought it back from my trip
and just kept it.

1546
00:56:41,008 --> 00:56:42,400
Whoa!

1547
00:56:42,400 --> 00:56:43,579
[Fully absorbed in self-content]

1548
00:56:43,579 --> 00:56:45,349
Awesome!

1549
00:56:46,262 --> 00:56:49,419
Good thing Seo Jun brought everything.

1550
00:56:49,419 --> 00:56:51,769
- I'm the only one using it though.
- What?

1551
00:56:51,769 --> 00:56:55,052
[So childish]

1552
00:56:55,671 --> 00:56:57,950
Writer, I...

1553
00:56:57,950 --> 00:57:00,422
I'll take this scarf off for a second.

1554
00:57:02,311 --> 00:57:03,696
It's actually clothes!

1555
00:57:03,696 --> 00:57:06,315
It's clothes, it's clothes!

1556
00:57:06,315 --> 00:57:07,955
[She was wearing a T-shirt like a scarf...]

1557
00:57:07,955 --> 00:57:10,724
This is clothing, this is actually clothes!

1558
00:57:11,422 --> 00:57:13,507
Woo Shik can wear that.

1559
00:57:13,507 --> 00:57:15,716
Can I use that as underwear?

1560
00:57:15,716 --> 00:57:19,519
[Yumi can't hear anything now]

1561
00:57:19,519 --> 00:57:21,899
That habit comes in handy now.

1562
00:57:21,899 --> 00:57:25,999
I usually just wear
this cotton T-shirt like a scarf.

1563
00:57:25,999 --> 00:57:27,970
Oh, this could be pajamas!

1564
00:57:27,970 --> 00:57:30,265
- Nice.
- Yay!

1565
00:57:30,940 --> 00:57:34,237
[Woo Shik's pick: the KTX travel guidebook]

1566
00:57:34,237 --> 00:57:36,779
Wow, where is this?

1567
00:57:36,779 --> 00:57:39,084
- Namwon, Jeonbuk.
- Jirisan Mountain, further south...

1568
00:57:39,084 --> 00:57:41,679
Jirisan Mountain? That sounds nice too.

1569
00:57:41,679 --> 00:57:45,839
Wanna go to Namwon?
I know someone who has a house there.

1570
00:57:45,839 --> 00:57:47,448
Can I stay there too?

1571
00:57:47,448 --> 00:57:49,728
- He owns the entire house.
- Yeah?

1572
00:57:49,728 --> 00:57:51,043
So this is Namwon here?

1573
00:57:51,043 --> 00:57:52,507
He keeps telling me to go to Namwon with him.

1574
00:57:52,507 --> 00:57:55,375
- Let's go! Let's go!
- Here...

1575
00:57:55,375 --> 00:57:58,134
Is using a connection okay?

1576
00:57:58,134 --> 00:58:01,250
Then I'll call him later
when we get a phone chance.

1577
00:58:01,250 --> 00:58:02,939
But does he actually live there?

1578
00:58:02,939 --> 00:58:05,250
- He just manages it.
- Let's go, let's go!

1579
00:58:05,250 --> 00:58:06,809
I'm shy... might not be able to talk to him.

1580
00:58:06,809 --> 00:58:08,878
Then you can sleep somewhere else.

1581
00:58:08,878 --> 00:58:10,930
- I'm going there.
- Let's go together.

1582
00:58:10,930 --> 00:58:12,985
- Namwon sounds good.
- Let's go to Namwon.

1583
00:58:12,985 --> 00:58:15,952
- Let's go to Namwon.
- Let me see.

1584
00:58:15,952 --> 00:58:17,887
At the foot of Jirisan Mountain.

1585
00:58:17,887 --> 00:58:20,160
So this is the plan?

1586
00:58:20,160 --> 00:58:21,819
Today, Daegu.

1587
00:58:21,819 --> 00:58:24,927
Then go from here to Namwon.

1588
00:58:24,927 --> 00:58:26,215
- And from Namwon...
- We'll have to take a bus.

1589
00:58:26,215 --> 00:58:28,139
From Namwon...

1590
00:58:30,433 --> 00:58:33,166
Let's plan to go to Namwon
and try contacting him first.

1591
00:58:33,166 --> 00:58:34,680
- Let's go with Namwon for now.
- Yeah.

1592
00:58:34,680 --> 00:58:38,593
- How much do we have left?
- We've got 150,000 won left in total...

1593
00:58:38,593 --> 00:58:40,467
but let's exclude the coins.

1594
00:58:40,467 --> 00:58:43,379
- 150,000...
- 151,000 won.

1595
00:58:43,379 --> 00:58:44,399
151,000 won.

1596
00:58:44,399 --> 00:58:46,714
It'll be hard to cover lodging with this.

1597
00:58:46,714 --> 00:58:48,517
Exactly.

1598
00:58:48,517 --> 00:58:51,921
Like, if it's a rural guesthouse kind of place,

1599
00:58:51,921 --> 00:58:55,758
even just a room and a living room...

1600
00:58:55,758 --> 00:58:57,973
But Dongdaegu is basically downtown,

1601
00:58:57,973 --> 00:59:00,038
so I wonder if places like that
even exist there.

1602
00:59:00,038 --> 00:59:03,494
And we can't even look it up without phones.

1603
00:59:04,336 --> 00:59:06,034
Ah, underwear...

1604
00:59:06,034 --> 00:59:08,771
[Woo Shik is more worried
about underwear than lodging]

1605
00:59:08,771 --> 00:59:11,974
Since Dongdaegu is downtown,
there might be something like that.

1606
00:59:11,974 --> 00:59:14,741
Places near the station
might actually be cheap.

1607
00:59:14,741 --> 00:59:15,904
- That could be true.
- Let's check it out.

1608
00:59:15,904 --> 00:59:18,047
There could be cheap places.

1609
00:59:18,047 --> 00:59:20,147
- We'll have to walk around and check.
- Yeah.

1610
00:59:20,147 --> 00:59:23,887
- Should we walk around near the station?
- Yeah.

1611
00:59:23,887 --> 00:59:25,821
[They decide to check places
near the station first]

1612
00:59:25,821 --> 00:59:28,124
Woo Shik, I don't think
we'll get to eat mungtigi today.

1613
00:59:28,124 --> 00:59:30,959
Yeah, probably not.

1614
00:59:30,959 --> 00:59:34,408
- It's expensive.
- No way we can afford it.

1615
00:59:34,408 --> 00:59:39,196
At this rate, we'll probably just end up
at some cheap gimbap place in Daegu.

1616
00:59:39,196 --> 00:59:42,039
[A future that somehow feels
completely predictable]

1617
00:59:42,039 --> 00:59:44,673
If we can even afford that...

1618
00:59:44,673 --> 00:59:50,116
But when you travel,
eating good food is the best part.

1619
00:59:50,116 --> 00:59:52,805
And we're kind of missing that.

1620
00:59:52,805 --> 00:59:55,940
Alright, let's decide this.

1621
00:59:55,940 --> 00:59:57,480
Look, we have three things to spend money on.

1622
00:59:57,480 --> 01:00:00,320
Transport, accommodation, and food.

1623
01:00:00,320 --> 01:00:01,599
- Right?
- Yeah.

1624
01:00:01,599 --> 01:00:03,914
Which one do you think is the most important?

1625
01:00:03,914 --> 01:00:06,495
- Wait, ask again.
- What's more important, sleep?

1626
01:00:06,495 --> 01:00:09,999
- Or eating good food?
- Food!

1627
01:00:09,999 --> 01:00:11,667
Food?

1628
01:00:11,667 --> 01:00:13,196
[Thinking...]

1629
01:00:13,196 --> 01:00:14,913
- For me, sleep.
- Sleep?

1630
01:00:14,913 --> 01:00:17,479
Then you and I are really different.

1631
01:00:17,479 --> 01:00:21,143
So you'd eat cheap food,
but still want to sleep somewhere nice.

1632
01:00:21,143 --> 01:00:22,629
Not necessarily a good place.

1633
01:00:22,629 --> 01:00:24,756
- I know.
- Not like a fancy place, I just mean...

1634
01:00:24,756 --> 01:00:27,489
- Just somewhere to sleep?
- Yeah.

1635
01:00:27,489 --> 01:00:30,529
I want to eat something good too.

1636
01:00:30,529 --> 01:00:33,119
So what's your priority?

1637
01:00:33,119 --> 01:00:35,031
I choose... food.

1638
01:00:35,031 --> 01:00:36,749
Me too.

1639
01:00:36,749 --> 01:00:38,102
Same, food.

1640
01:00:38,102 --> 01:00:40,545
[Laughing]

1641
01:00:40,545 --> 01:00:42,616
Is that really true?

1642
01:00:42,616 --> 01:00:44,794
You're not going to grant my wish anyway.

1643
01:00:44,794 --> 01:00:46,089
- No, no.
- We will.

1644
01:00:46,089 --> 01:00:48,396
You're 44, so we should listen to you.

1645
01:00:48,396 --> 01:00:49,642
Oh right, you're "Po-po (44)."

1646
01:00:49,642 --> 01:00:52,036
Right, you're the oldest here.
You're in your forties.

1647
01:00:52,036 --> 01:00:54,779
"Po-po". Big sis "Po-po."

1648
01:00:56,245 --> 01:00:58,147
- Ah, my stomach...
- Who drank this?

1649
01:00:58,147 --> 01:01:01,695
- He drank it all.
- I never even opened it.

1650
01:01:01,695 --> 01:01:04,186
Is it leaking or something?

1651
01:01:04,186 --> 01:01:06,802
[Actually, Woo Shik...]

1652
01:01:06,802 --> 01:01:08,148
I'm tired.

1653
01:01:08,148 --> 01:01:10,196
[Right after getting on the train,
he gulps once]

1654
01:01:10,196 --> 01:01:11,723
I don't think we'll find a guesthouse.

1655
01:01:11,723 --> 01:01:13,560
[He gulps even when Seo Jun is worried]

1656
01:01:13,560 --> 01:01:16,009
Say you'll drink first, then drink.

1657
01:01:16,009 --> 01:01:18,604
Oh right, we were sharing this.

1658
01:01:18,604 --> 01:01:21,125
I didn't drink from it directly.

1659
01:01:22,416 --> 01:01:24,203
[He actually drank from it]

1660
01:01:24,203 --> 01:01:26,528
[Checking remaining water]

1661
01:01:26,528 --> 01:01:28,811
[Awkward]

1662
01:01:28,811 --> 01:01:32,852
[In the end, the last sip goes to Woo Shik...]

1663
01:01:32,852 --> 01:01:35,123
It's 1,000 won per bottle.

1664
01:01:37,016 --> 01:01:40,051
[It was basically Woo Shik's water]

1665
01:01:41,039 --> 01:01:43,237
What the heck?

1666
01:01:43,237 --> 01:01:45,490
- Oh my.
- What is it?

1667
01:01:45,490 --> 01:01:48,651
[What unfolds before their eyes right now...]

1668
01:01:48,651 --> 01:01:49,929
Whoa...

1669
01:01:49,929 --> 01:01:52,635
Wow, where are we?

1670
01:01:52,635 --> 01:01:53,884
Hey, isn't this Gumi?

1671
01:01:53,884 --> 01:01:55,369
[An unexpected heavy snowfall]

1672
01:01:55,369 --> 01:01:58,180
This is more beautiful than midwinter.

1673
01:01:59,112 --> 01:02:01,730
- It's snowing right now.
- Yeah, it's snowing.

1674
01:02:01,730 --> 01:02:04,146
It's snowing...

1675
01:02:04,146 --> 01:02:07,113
Oh my, the mountains are beautiful.

1676
01:02:07,113 --> 01:02:09,259
Wow, snow!

1677
01:02:09,259 --> 01:02:10,365
Is this real?

1678
01:02:10,365 --> 01:02:11,971
[Snow they encountered at the end of February]

1679
01:02:11,971 --> 01:02:15,991
Is this real?

1680
01:02:20,722 --> 01:02:22,271
Wow...

1681
01:02:23,499 --> 01:02:25,784
We're not going north, right?

1682
01:02:25,784 --> 01:02:28,270
Did we get on the wrong train?

1683
01:02:28,270 --> 01:02:31,415
[As they get closer to Daegu]

1684
01:02:31,415 --> 01:02:35,725
[The snowstorm gets stronger]

1685
01:02:35,725 --> 01:02:38,238
We've arrived. This is Dongdaegu.

1686
01:02:39,072 --> 01:02:40,240
You've got a hat, right?

1687
01:02:40,240 --> 01:02:43,013
- In March...
- Whoa, what... it's snowing?

1688
01:02:44,616 --> 01:02:49,043
[Not the Daegu they knew]

1689
01:02:49,043 --> 01:02:53,993
[They arrived in Daegu,
strangely blanketed in white snow]

1690
01:02:53,993 --> 01:02:56,809
Oh, Daegu Station. It's been a while.

1691
01:02:56,809 --> 01:02:59,256
- It's really snowing a lot.
- Oh my, oh my.

1692
01:02:59,256 --> 01:03:00,345
Oh my.

1693
01:03:00,345 --> 01:03:04,232
- Does it usually snow like this here?
- Right?

1694
01:03:04,232 --> 01:03:06,799
- Oh, are you from Daegu?
- Yes.

1695
01:03:06,799 --> 01:03:08,640
Does it usually snow this much in Daegu?

1696
01:03:08,640 --> 01:03:09,678
- No.
- Right?

1697
01:03:09,678 --> 01:03:11,106
- It's my first time.
- She is pretty friendly.

1698
01:03:11,106 --> 01:03:12,253
It's been years.

1699
01:03:12,253 --> 01:03:13,257
- Years?
- Yes.

1700
01:03:13,257 --> 01:03:14,359
- Oh my!
- Wow...

1701
01:03:14,359 --> 01:03:16,599
- Do you know her?
- No.

1702
01:03:16,599 --> 01:03:18,683
- She's from Daegu.
- Oh.

1703
01:03:18,683 --> 01:03:22,185
You said it's been a long time
since it snowed like this in Daegu, right?

1704
01:03:22,185 --> 01:03:23,698
- Yes.
- Oh my, what do we do?

1705
01:03:23,698 --> 01:03:25,184
Wow...

1706
01:03:25,184 --> 01:03:27,004
- Wow!
- Wow, wow, wow!

1707
01:03:27,004 --> 01:03:28,837
[Finally, time to step out into the world!]
It's kind of...

1708
01:03:28,837 --> 01:03:29,994
- What should we do?
- Hey...

1709
01:03:29,994 --> 01:03:31,332
What is this?

1710
01:03:31,332 --> 01:03:32,899
[What unfolds before their eyes...]
What is this?

1711
01:03:32,899 --> 01:03:35,127
- What is this?
- Oh my.

1712
01:03:35,127 --> 01:03:36,708
[Huge snowstorm]

1713
01:03:36,708 --> 01:03:38,630
Oh my, oh my.

1714
01:03:41,005 --> 01:03:42,389
[Facing it head-on]

1715
01:03:42,389 --> 01:03:44,680
- Use this together.
- It's okay, we're fine.

1716
01:03:44,680 --> 01:03:48,839
Do you happen to know any cheap places
to stay around here?

1717
01:03:48,839 --> 01:03:50,135
- Cheap lodging?
- Yes.

1718
01:03:50,135 --> 01:03:51,535
- They're all cheap around here.
- She says they're all cheap.

1719
01:03:51,535 --> 01:03:53,328
They're all cheap. Let's go.

1720
01:03:53,328 --> 01:03:55,981
I'm... I'm okay, thank you!

1721
01:03:55,981 --> 01:03:58,214
Thank you!

1722
01:04:00,074 --> 01:04:01,797
Oh, thank you!

1723
01:04:01,797 --> 01:04:04,281
- We're good, really.
- Okay, okay.

1724
01:04:04,281 --> 01:04:06,638
- Thank you!
- She says they're all cheap.

1725
01:04:06,638 --> 01:04:09,669
So... how do we find a place to stay?

1726
01:04:09,669 --> 01:04:11,662
City tour... wait.

1727
01:04:11,662 --> 01:04:14,009
[They want to look it up,
but they don't have their phones...]

1728
01:04:14,009 --> 01:04:15,870
- First of all...
- Should we go to the info desk?

1729
01:04:15,870 --> 01:04:17,167
Yeah, we should go to the info desk.

1730
01:04:17,167 --> 01:04:19,187
- Am I dreaming since this morning?
- There it is, there it is.

1731
01:04:19,187 --> 01:04:22,527
- "Tourist information desk."
- Oh, there it is!

1732
01:04:22,527 --> 01:04:23,529
Wow!

1733
01:04:23,529 --> 01:04:26,195
[Found the Dongdaegu
Tourist Information Center]

1734
01:04:26,894 --> 01:04:28,920
Hey...

1735
01:04:29,889 --> 01:04:32,895
This is totally unexpected.

1736
01:04:32,895 --> 01:04:34,124
What is this?

1737
01:04:34,124 --> 01:04:35,907
What is happening?

1738
01:04:35,907 --> 01:04:37,739
What is this?

1739
01:04:37,739 --> 01:04:39,798
My clothes are going to get soaked.

1740
01:04:39,798 --> 01:04:42,961
[Of all days, it had to snow today]

1741
01:04:42,961 --> 01:04:44,698
Aah!

1742
01:04:47,312 --> 01:04:48,406
Should we go in?

1743
01:04:48,406 --> 01:04:50,002
[Hesitating at the entrance...]

1744
01:04:50,002 --> 01:04:51,008
Okay.

1745
01:04:51,008 --> 01:04:52,226
[Let's go]

1746
01:04:52,226 --> 01:04:53,932
Oh, it's warm inside.

1747
01:04:54,883 --> 01:04:56,536
Hello!

1748
01:04:56,536 --> 01:05:01,023
- Hello,
- We... in Daegu...

1749
01:05:01,023 --> 01:05:05,491
We're trying to find a place to stay.

1750
01:05:05,491 --> 01:05:07,551
- Relatively cheap...
- Oh, I see a hotel here.

1751
01:05:07,551 --> 01:05:11,233
Not just relatively cheap,
we're looking for somewhere really affordable.

1752
01:05:11,233 --> 01:05:12,979
[Seo Jun stepped up bravely]
Right.

1753
01:05:12,979 --> 01:05:14,925
There are several

1754
01:05:14,925 --> 01:05:18,173
lodging options in this area.

1755
01:05:18,173 --> 01:05:21,517
We've gathered some of the cheaper options.

1756
01:05:21,517 --> 01:05:23,494
Hey, should we just go to a jjimjilbang?

1757
01:05:23,494 --> 01:05:25,710
A jjimjilbang would be super cheap.

1758
01:05:25,710 --> 01:05:29,101
That's in the downtown area, around Banwoldang.

1759
01:05:29,101 --> 01:05:32,721
Or there's a place called "Mu*** Inn"
that includes breakfast.

1760
01:05:32,721 --> 01:05:34,857
Breakfast is a luxury for us.

1761
01:05:34,857 --> 01:05:36,525
They provide free meals.

1762
01:05:36,525 --> 01:05:38,293
Meals are included.

1763
01:05:38,293 --> 01:05:39,898
- Oh?
- Oh!

1764
01:05:39,898 --> 01:05:40,919
That sounds pretty good.

1765
01:05:40,919 --> 01:05:42,632
It's right behind there.

1766
01:05:42,632 --> 01:05:43,803
- Oh really?
- Oh, there it is!

1767
01:05:43,803 --> 01:05:45,067
- There it is!
- Sorry!

1768
01:05:45,067 --> 01:05:47,088
- Mu*** Inn.
- There it is!

1769
01:05:47,088 --> 01:05:49,307
- Let's go there now.
- Where?

1770
01:05:49,307 --> 01:05:51,227
- Right in front of us here.
- There's a big screen there.

1771
01:05:51,227 --> 01:05:52,374
Oh, there? Yeah, I see it.

1772
01:05:52,374 --> 01:05:54,506
- Let's go!
- Let's go check it out! We're going there.

1773
01:05:54,506 --> 01:05:56,362
- But for one room...
- Thank you!

1774
01:05:56,362 --> 01:05:58,414
- Thank you.
- Thank you, thank you!

1775
01:05:58,414 --> 01:06:00,582
If you're going there,

1776
01:06:00,582 --> 01:06:02,727
you can take the escalator down.

1777
01:06:02,727 --> 01:06:05,788
- Oh, yes.
- Go down and keep walking to the left.

1778
01:06:05,788 --> 01:06:07,189
- That's awesome.
- Oh, like that?

1779
01:06:07,189 --> 01:06:08,510
Thank you.

1780
01:06:08,510 --> 01:06:10,584
- Happy Lunar New Year!
- Be careful.

1781
01:06:10,584 --> 01:06:12,602
- My pants...
- Watch your step, it's slippery.

1782
01:06:12,602 --> 01:06:14,845
You be careful too.

1783
01:06:16,030 --> 01:06:17,935
Oh, be careful!

1784
01:06:18,664 --> 01:06:20,318
Wow, I'm completely soaked.

1785
01:06:20,318 --> 01:06:22,141
It's freezing.

1786
01:06:22,141 --> 01:06:23,903
Aah!

1787
01:06:23,903 --> 01:06:25,973
- Careful!
- Hey, let's stick together.

1788
01:06:25,973 --> 01:06:29,315
[Camaraderie blooming in the midst of crisis]

1789
01:06:29,315 --> 01:06:31,319
- But...
- Yeah.

1790
01:06:31,319 --> 01:06:33,925
- It's not like this was planned or anything.
- Yeah.

1791
01:06:33,925 --> 01:06:35,984
The accommodation too.

1792
01:06:35,984 --> 01:06:37,574
- How did we end up on our way there?
- Exactly.

1793
01:06:37,574 --> 01:06:42,798
But it feels like the accommodation
is over 60,000 won per room.

1794
01:06:43,679 --> 01:06:44,932
Opening video...

1795
01:06:44,932 --> 01:06:49,945
No, we were trying to start off cool
in our opening outfits...

1796
01:06:50,632 --> 01:06:52,301
[Ended up looking like snowmen...]

1797
01:06:52,301 --> 01:06:55,089
But at least the footage actually
looks pretty good though?

1798
01:06:55,089 --> 01:06:59,130
- Right.
- Who knew it would snow in Daegu?

1799
01:06:59,922 --> 01:07:01,613
[Ignorance is a sin]

1800
01:07:01,613 --> 01:07:03,078
Wow.

1801
01:07:03,078 --> 01:07:06,519
Wow, my socks are completely soaked.

1802
01:07:07,483 --> 01:07:09,596
We need to buy socks too.

1803
01:07:11,329 --> 01:07:14,089
[Arrived at Mu*** Inn]

1804
01:07:14,089 --> 01:07:15,849
Please check first,
and if it's okay, we'll come in.

1805
01:07:15,849 --> 01:07:18,135
- Is filming allowed here?
- Yes.

1806
01:07:18,135 --> 01:07:19,292
Hello.

1807
01:07:19,292 --> 01:07:22,546
[Will they be able to find accommodation
in one shot?]

1808
01:07:23,999 --> 01:07:25,591
This place is nice though.

1809
01:07:25,591 --> 01:07:27,021
It has a good vibe.

1810
01:07:27,021 --> 01:07:28,886
[Filming permission secured for now]

1811
01:07:28,886 --> 01:07:30,672
I'm nervous.

1812
01:07:30,672 --> 01:07:31,975
May I have your name?

1813
01:07:31,975 --> 01:07:33,742
Oh, we didn't make a reservation...

1814
01:07:33,742 --> 01:07:36,635
- We're fully booked.
- Oh, really?

1815
01:07:36,635 --> 01:07:38,554
Ah...

1816
01:07:38,554 --> 01:07:40,682
- That's a bust.
- Did you bring it?

1817
01:07:40,682 --> 01:07:45,091
Excuse me, are there any inns nearby?

1818
01:07:45,091 --> 01:07:46,889
- There's a motel right next door...
- Okay.

1819
01:07:46,889 --> 01:07:49,939
but I'm not sure
about the price or availability.

1820
01:07:49,939 --> 01:07:52,519
- Okay...
- Okay, thank you!

1821
01:07:52,519 --> 01:07:54,399
Should we try next door?

1822
01:07:55,619 --> 01:07:58,200
I thought things were finally going our way.

1823
01:07:58,200 --> 01:08:00,489
[Moving to the next option]

1824
01:08:00,489 --> 01:08:02,945
Oh, it's right next door.

1825
01:08:04,269 --> 01:08:07,075
[Second walk-in attempt]

1826
01:08:07,075 --> 01:08:08,994
Oh, here's an inn...

1827
01:08:09,821 --> 01:08:11,213
Hello.

1828
01:08:11,213 --> 01:08:12,958
- Do you have any rooms available?
- Yes!

1829
01:08:12,958 --> 01:08:14,245
- You do?
- Yes.

1830
01:08:14,245 --> 01:08:16,664
[Finally found an available room]

1831
01:08:16,664 --> 01:08:19,370
- We should ask that.
- Oh, by the way, we're currently filming...

1832
01:08:19,370 --> 01:08:21,519
- Is it okay if we film here?
- What kind of filming is this?

1833
01:08:21,519 --> 01:08:25,561
We're from tvN's "Let's Travel Without Money,"

1834
01:08:25,561 --> 01:08:27,633
and we're supposed to travel without money.

1835
01:08:27,633 --> 01:08:29,001
- Travel without money?
- Yes.

1836
01:08:29,001 --> 01:08:31,254
- Per day...
- We have to keep it cheap.

1837
01:08:31,254 --> 01:08:32,434
[For now, they go all in on acting pitiful]

1838
01:08:32,434 --> 01:08:34,464
One moment, please...

1839
01:08:34,464 --> 01:08:37,179
Wait, aren't you Park Seo Jun?

1840
01:08:37,179 --> 01:08:39,358
- That's right.
- Yes, that's right.

1841
01:08:39,358 --> 01:08:41,625
How have you been?

1842
01:08:41,625 --> 01:08:43,048
[They even start using flirting tactics]

1843
01:08:43,048 --> 01:08:45,959
Daegu is like my second hometown.

1844
01:08:45,959 --> 01:08:48,760
But I'm not exactly sure
what kind of filming this is.

1845
01:08:48,760 --> 01:08:51,550
- Oh, it's just like this.
- This is all we do.

1846
01:08:51,550 --> 01:08:53,510
- Rooms, two rooms.
- Two rooms.

1847
01:08:53,510 --> 01:08:57,068
- Yes.
- There's also me.

1848
01:08:57,068 --> 01:08:58,175
- I'm...
- Ah, Yumi?

1849
01:08:58,175 --> 01:08:59,208
- Yes.
- Yes.

1850
01:08:59,208 --> 01:09:00,621
- I need a separate room.
- Say hello quickly.

1851
01:09:00,621 --> 01:09:01,930
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you.

1852
01:09:01,930 --> 01:09:05,637
The thing is,
they will share one room, and I...

1853
01:09:05,637 --> 01:09:07,238
- Oh, separately?
- Yes.

1854
01:09:07,238 --> 01:09:08,971
Two share one, and one alone.

1855
01:09:08,971 --> 01:09:12,171
But the most important thing is the price...

1856
01:09:12,171 --> 01:09:14,299
How much is the room?

1857
01:09:14,299 --> 01:09:16,478
We don't have much money, so...

1858
01:09:16,478 --> 01:09:19,314
Well, the standard room is 60,000 won each.

1859
01:09:19,314 --> 01:09:20,675
60,000 won each? Okay...

1860
01:09:20,675 --> 01:09:21,853
- 60,000 won and 50,000 won?
- Pardon?

1861
01:09:21,853 --> 01:09:23,041
60,000 won, 50,000 won!

1862
01:09:23,041 --> 01:09:24,086
Oh, 60,000 won and 50,000 won?

1863
01:09:24,086 --> 01:09:25,092
- 60,000 won!
- No, 60,000 won.

1864
01:09:25,092 --> 01:09:26,303
60,000 won and 50,000 won!

1865
01:09:26,303 --> 01:09:28,723
No, since it's you two, 60,000 won,
and mine is 50,000 won.

1866
01:09:28,723 --> 01:09:30,839
Huh? Is that right?

1867
01:09:30,839 --> 01:09:32,479
- Did I hear that wrong?
- That's what she said...

1868
01:09:32,479 --> 01:09:34,585
- No, it's 60,000 won each.
- 60,000 won, 60,000 won.

1869
01:09:34,585 --> 01:09:37,234
- Maybe I can at least knock off 10,000 won...
- At least try saying...

1870
01:09:37,234 --> 01:09:39,267
- That won't work. That's not allowed.
- No...

1871
01:09:39,267 --> 01:09:41,903
- Well, I'm just an employee, so...
- Okay.

1872
01:09:41,903 --> 01:09:45,020
- I'll ask the owner.
- Please just ask once.

1873
01:09:45,020 --> 01:09:47,172
Alright, then feel free to ask...

1874
01:09:47,172 --> 01:09:48,235
- Sorry.
- Yeah.

1875
01:09:48,235 --> 01:09:50,579
I thought it was 60,000 won and 50,000 won.

1876
01:09:50,579 --> 01:09:53,448
If it's 60,000 won each, that's 120,000 won,
then we'd have 30,000 won left.

1877
01:09:53,448 --> 01:09:55,453
We could each get a bowl
of gukbap at the market.

1878
01:09:55,453 --> 01:09:57,197
I want to have codfish soup too...

1879
01:09:57,197 --> 01:09:59,801
But getting to the market is also a problem.

1880
01:10:03,625 --> 01:10:06,024
- Ah, yes, yes. Sir.
- Oh, thank you!

1881
01:10:06,024 --> 01:10:07,691
Did we reach a dramatic agreement?

1882
01:10:07,691 --> 01:10:10,198
[Owner's approval granted]

1883
01:10:10,198 --> 01:10:12,897
So earlier, she said 60,000 won and 50,000 won?

1884
01:10:12,897 --> 01:10:14,670
60,000 won each.

1885
01:10:14,670 --> 01:10:16,758
Oh! Could I get your autograph?

1886
01:10:16,758 --> 01:10:20,299
Oh dear, I'd do an autograph
for 40,000 won but...

1887
01:10:20,299 --> 01:10:22,663
Our autograph fee is usually 40,000 won.

1888
01:10:22,663 --> 01:10:24,359
Right.

1889
01:10:24,359 --> 01:10:26,368
Sometimes it's even more expensive.

1890
01:10:26,368 --> 01:10:27,382
Yeah.

1891
01:10:27,382 --> 01:10:29,475
We do sell them, but... yeah.

1892
01:10:29,475 --> 01:10:30,560
Here...

1893
01:10:30,560 --> 01:10:32,863
- Thank you!
- No problem.

1894
01:10:34,656 --> 01:10:36,114
Oh right, ma'am.

1895
01:10:36,114 --> 01:10:37,960
Are there any...

1896
01:10:37,960 --> 01:10:40,952
nearby markets around here?

1897
01:10:40,952 --> 01:10:44,882
There's Pyeonghwa Market's
chicken gizzards alley!

1898
01:10:44,882 --> 01:10:46,702
- Chicken gizzards alley?
- Chicken gizzards alley?

1899
01:10:46,702 --> 01:10:48,742
It's quite famous.

1900
01:10:48,742 --> 01:10:52,641
We don't have phones, so we can't look it up...

1901
01:10:52,641 --> 01:10:55,674
Do the rooms have computers?

1902
01:10:55,674 --> 01:10:56,778
- Yes, they do.
- Oh!

1903
01:10:56,778 --> 01:10:57,846
Let's search for it.

1904
01:10:57,846 --> 01:11:00,565
We'll greet you again later, thank you!

1905
01:11:00,565 --> 01:11:02,274
- Can we go to our rooms now?
- This place is really nice!

1906
01:11:02,274 --> 01:11:04,019
Thank you!

1907
01:11:04,019 --> 01:11:05,719
- Let's go up first.
- Thank you.

1908
01:11:05,719 --> 01:11:08,556
This place is really good!

1909
01:11:08,556 --> 01:11:10,710
[Right after the trio secured their lodging...]

1910
01:11:10,710 --> 01:11:12,205
Sir!

1911
01:11:12,205 --> 01:11:14,479
[The staff also booked the same floor]
Are there more rooms on the 5th floor?

1912
01:11:15,397 --> 01:11:16,772
[Cast & crew successfully
secured their first walk-in stay]

1913
01:11:16,772 --> 01:11:19,097
Wow!

1914
01:11:19,932 --> 01:11:23,093
- Yours is 507.
- Yeah, I'll go check your room first.

1915
01:11:23,976 --> 01:11:25,596
Oh, water! Water!

1916
01:11:25,596 --> 01:11:28,176
- Water?
- Lots of water!

1917
01:11:28,176 --> 01:11:29,544
- 500...
- Room 507!

1918
01:11:29,544 --> 01:11:31,189
507 comes first. Let's check here.

1919
01:11:31,189 --> 01:11:32,871
Is this your room? Oh, it's mine.

1920
01:11:32,871 --> 01:11:35,819
[Checking Yumi's room first]

1921
01:11:35,819 --> 01:11:39,045
- Oh, nice, nice!
- Let me put my bag down.

1922
01:11:39,045 --> 01:11:41,258
Wow, my room is awesome!

1923
01:11:41,258 --> 01:11:42,350
Shall we check room 503?

1924
01:11:42,350 --> 01:11:45,327
[Now it's time to check
Seo Jun and Woo Shik's room]

1925
01:11:45,327 --> 01:11:48,359
Oh, hey!

1926
01:11:48,359 --> 01:11:49,889
This is great!

1927
01:11:49,889 --> 01:11:51,603
- Oh!
- Nice!

1928
01:11:51,603 --> 01:11:53,368
It's like an internet cafe!

1929
01:11:53,368 --> 01:11:55,767
- Hey, what is this?
- We got a good room.

1930
01:11:55,767 --> 01:11:58,309
- What a good room!
- This is so nice!

1931
01:11:58,309 --> 01:12:00,590
[Point 1: two computers]

1932
01:12:00,590 --> 01:12:02,570
[Point 2: spacious and clean]

1933
01:12:02,570 --> 01:12:05,042
[Point 3: free water, coffee,
cereal, and toast]

1934
01:12:05,042 --> 01:12:07,463
[Point 4: near Dongdaegu Station]

1935
01:12:07,463 --> 01:12:09,951
[Overall score: five stars]

1936
01:12:09,951 --> 01:12:12,818
I feel like we used up
all our luck at the start.

1937
01:12:12,818 --> 01:12:14,280
["We've used up way too much luck
on this place." - Actress Jung Yumi]

1938
01:12:14,280 --> 01:12:15,421
I even thought about that.

1939
01:12:15,421 --> 01:12:20,439
We got lucky today and ended up
staying somewhere this nice.

1940
01:12:20,439 --> 01:12:24,005
If it's like a guesthouse,
two rooms wouldn't even be available.

1941
01:12:24,005 --> 01:12:26,753
In that case, even just a room
and a living room...

1942
01:12:26,753 --> 01:12:29,519
that would probably be enough for us to stay.

1943
01:12:29,519 --> 01:12:33,729
But somehow, I feel like
we'll keep staying at nice places...

1944
01:12:33,729 --> 01:12:37,649
[Yumi's confidence has skyrocketed]

1945
01:12:37,649 --> 01:12:39,248
- Wow, I'm so relieved.
- This is so nice.

1946
01:12:39,248 --> 01:12:40,348
This is great.

1947
01:12:40,348 --> 01:12:44,167
- Alright, let's search first.
- Wait, let's sit for a bit first.

1948
01:12:45,271 --> 01:12:48,323
- This is amazing.
- Wow, this is awesome.

1949
01:12:48,323 --> 01:12:51,099
"Dongdaegu Station food spots!"

1950
01:12:51,099 --> 01:12:52,194
"Nearby good restaurants."

1951
01:12:52,194 --> 01:12:53,677
Try searching "good restaurants." Nearby spots.

1952
01:12:53,677 --> 01:12:56,297
We can just go nearby, right?

1953
01:12:57,165 --> 01:13:01,102
But we can't really go to nice restaurants...
we only have 30,000 won.

1954
01:13:01,102 --> 01:13:03,605
Hey, we said we'd go to the market.

1955
01:13:03,605 --> 01:13:05,935
- Pyeonghwa Market... where was that?
- But...

1956
01:13:05,935 --> 01:13:09,901
- Pyeonghwa Market. Chicken gizzards alley.
- It's here.

1957
01:13:09,901 --> 01:13:11,971
So it's from here to here.

1958
01:13:11,971 --> 01:13:13,936
- We can walk there, right?
- Yeah.

1959
01:13:13,936 --> 01:13:16,605
- It's close.
- Then, the market... what time is it now?

1960
01:13:16,605 --> 01:13:18,941
But everything here is...
basically chicken gizzards.

1961
01:13:18,941 --> 01:13:21,189
Yeah, that's what this place is famous for.

1962
01:13:21,189 --> 01:13:22,479
[About 10 minutes later]

1963
01:13:22,479 --> 01:13:25,557
- We should go to an old local spot.
- Yeah, a proper old restaurant.

1964
01:13:25,557 --> 01:13:29,294
- There's beef gukbap for 4,500 won.
- Where?

1965
01:13:29,294 --> 01:13:31,115
At Pyeonghwa Market,
there are still places selling

1966
01:13:31,115 --> 01:13:32,467
- beef gukbap for 5,000 won...
- Oh.

1967
01:13:32,467 --> 01:13:34,015
You even get change back

1968
01:13:34,015 --> 01:13:35,240
- from a 5,000 won bill...
- Wow!

1969
01:13:35,240 --> 01:13:36,886
- Wow!
- This looks good.

1970
01:13:36,886 --> 01:13:38,663
It's perfect for a hangover...
really hits the spot.

1971
01:13:38,663 --> 01:13:42,586
The menu's diverse too, so I ordered
tteokbokki, sundae, and dakgangjeong.

1972
01:13:42,586 --> 01:13:44,120
Especially the dakgangjeong...

1973
01:13:44,120 --> 01:13:45,925
Oh, this place looks good.

1974
01:13:45,925 --> 01:13:48,646
- Okay, let's go to "Jang*** Mukbang."
- "Jang*** Mukbang."

1975
01:13:48,646 --> 01:13:50,952
- Yumi, we looked it up.
- Yeah.

1976
01:13:50,952 --> 01:13:53,712
- There's a place called "Jang*** Mukbang."
- Let's go.

1977
01:13:53,712 --> 01:13:57,167
- Beef gukbap is 4,500 won.
- They have ramyeon too.

1978
01:13:57,167 --> 01:14:00,112
Let's go. Let's eat everything, even ramyeon.

1979
01:14:00,112 --> 01:14:01,743
Let's go!

1980
01:14:01,743 --> 01:14:04,633
[Time to dive back into a world
without the internet]

1981
01:14:04,633 --> 01:14:07,035
- Oh my gosh!
- Wow, it's snowing more!

1982
01:14:07,035 --> 01:14:09,402
- Hey, put your hat on.
- Okay.

1983
01:14:09,402 --> 01:14:11,439
[To make matters worse...]

1984
01:14:11,439 --> 01:14:14,043
[The snowstorm gets stronger]

1985
01:14:14,043 --> 01:14:17,609
[Snow is falling so heavily
it's hard to see ahead...]

1986
01:14:17,609 --> 01:14:21,364
[Can they really find their way
without phones?]

1987
01:14:21,364 --> 01:14:22,811
- We need to go that way.
- Yeah.

1988
01:14:22,811 --> 01:14:24,555
[Departure]

1989
01:14:24,555 --> 01:14:27,026
- That's an uphill slope, Seo Jun.
- That's a steep climb.

1990
01:14:27,026 --> 01:14:29,001
Let's go this way.

1991
01:14:29,981 --> 01:14:34,279
Hey, Dubai chewy cookie!

1992
01:14:34,279 --> 01:14:35,939
I'm more mint chocolate though...

1993
01:14:35,939 --> 01:14:37,807
That's some Dubai chewy cookie outfit.

1994
01:14:37,807 --> 01:14:39,938
Because of the brown...

1995
01:14:39,938 --> 01:14:43,093
[Dubai chewy cookie #1
pulls out the camcorder again]

1996
01:14:45,444 --> 01:14:47,009
Oh, oh... Where's Woo Shik?

1997
01:14:47,009 --> 01:14:48,698
I thought Woo Shik was over there.

1998
01:14:48,698 --> 01:14:51,377
[A chaotic move through the snowstorm]

1999
01:14:51,377 --> 01:14:55,581
- But it is really cold.
- Right? Your legs must be freezing.

2000
01:15:00,168 --> 01:15:02,310
Pa** Hospital!

2001
01:15:02,310 --> 01:15:03,504
Oh, there it is.

2002
01:15:03,504 --> 01:15:06,877
They said to turn left there.

2003
01:15:06,877 --> 01:15:09,723
Crunch.

2004
01:15:09,723 --> 01:15:12,267
I never thought we'd end up
walking on snow here...

2005
01:15:12,267 --> 01:15:14,613
What is going on right now?

2006
01:15:14,613 --> 01:15:15,861
[Info: Filming was on Feb 24,
spring weather until the day before]

2007
01:15:15,861 --> 01:15:16,866
This scene is hilarious.

2008
01:15:16,866 --> 01:15:18,400
I mean...

2009
01:15:19,274 --> 01:15:21,934
Oh no, our shoes are getting soaked.

2010
01:15:21,934 --> 01:15:24,412
- These are our only shoes.
- Yeah.

2011
01:15:24,412 --> 01:15:26,627
[Obvious]

2012
01:15:30,855 --> 01:15:32,809
[Yumi drained again]
Be careful.

2013
01:15:32,809 --> 01:15:34,591
Let's stick together.

2014
01:15:34,591 --> 01:15:37,197
- Huh?
- Stay close, it's slippery.

2015
01:15:37,197 --> 01:15:39,430
- Constantly...
- If one person slips, we're all...

2016
01:15:39,430 --> 01:15:40,716
[Laughing]

2017
01:15:40,716 --> 01:15:43,267
- we're all going down together.
- Yeah, all of us.

2018
01:15:47,646 --> 01:15:49,316
I can't feel my toes.

2019
01:15:49,316 --> 01:15:51,729
Me too, my toes...

2020
01:15:52,507 --> 01:15:55,897
Does it usually snow like this in Daegu?

2021
01:15:57,330 --> 01:15:58,656
- No way, right?
- This is insane...

2022
01:15:58,656 --> 01:16:02,139
- My feet are sinking in!
- This is crazy.

2023
01:16:03,985 --> 01:16:06,064
- Hey, hey, hey!
- Hey!

2024
01:16:06,064 --> 01:16:09,800
Hey, don't! If you fall, we're all in trouble.

2025
01:16:10,392 --> 01:16:12,018
I thought...

2026
01:16:12,018 --> 01:16:15,867
this was going to be a cool, stylish trip.

2027
01:16:15,867 --> 01:16:17,273
Me too...

2028
01:16:18,495 --> 01:16:20,422
It's all slushy.

2029
01:16:21,703 --> 01:16:25,571
- "The god of gukbap."
- Where is it?

2030
01:16:25,571 --> 01:16:28,366
Wow, that looks seriously delicious.
Look at that.

2031
01:16:28,366 --> 01:16:30,326
- Where?
- Here, the picture.

2032
01:16:30,326 --> 01:16:32,233
Wow.

2033
01:16:32,233 --> 01:16:35,006
[They swallow their saliva,
eyeing the food they can't have...]

2034
01:16:35,006 --> 01:16:37,057
But going to the market was a good idea.

2035
01:16:37,057 --> 01:16:38,500
Yeah.

2036
01:16:39,784 --> 01:16:42,685
I mean, if it's only 4,500 won,
we've gotta try it.

2037
01:16:42,685 --> 01:16:45,440
- Oh, it was 4,500 won?
- Yeah.

2038
01:16:48,576 --> 01:16:50,455
Feels like we're almost there.

2039
01:16:51,523 --> 01:16:52,817
- Oh, is it here?
- Oh!

2040
01:16:52,817 --> 01:16:54,306
No, wait. They said to turn
when we see the ENT clinic.

2041
01:16:54,306 --> 01:16:56,660
It's the entrance, the entrance!

2042
01:16:57,468 --> 01:17:01,249
- This is chicken gizzards alley, Woo Shik.
- Let's go in here.

2043
01:17:01,249 --> 01:17:04,551
[Finally entering Pyeonghwa Market]

2044
01:17:05,189 --> 01:17:07,619
Chicken gizzards alley.

2045
01:17:07,619 --> 01:17:09,177
Where exactly are we going?

2046
01:17:09,177 --> 01:17:11,055
Yumi, come this way.

2047
01:17:12,204 --> 01:17:13,397
It's not closed, right?

2048
01:17:13,397 --> 01:17:15,894
If not, we can just go somewhere like this.

2049
01:17:15,894 --> 01:17:17,542
Wow!

2050
01:17:17,542 --> 01:17:18,874
Oh, watch your step!

2051
01:17:18,874 --> 01:17:20,826
- Wow, this place is... kind of a mess.
- Watch your step.

2052
01:17:20,826 --> 01:17:21,901
Oh, no!

2053
01:17:21,901 --> 01:17:23,589
[Through an unbelievably muddy path]

2054
01:17:23,589 --> 01:17:25,724
Let's turn this way!

2055
01:17:25,724 --> 01:17:27,569
- Huh?
- Left.

2056
01:17:27,569 --> 01:17:28,967
Where is it?

2057
01:17:28,967 --> 01:17:32,023
[About 15 minutes into walking...]

2058
01:17:32,023 --> 01:17:34,359
- Here it is!
- Here it is! This is it!

2059
01:17:34,359 --> 01:17:37,716
[Finally found a restaurant]
Oh!

2060
01:17:37,716 --> 01:17:40,782
[Target spotted]

2061
01:17:40,782 --> 01:17:43,390
- Hello?
- Hello?

2062
01:17:43,390 --> 01:17:45,012
Would it be okay if we just film while eating?

2063
01:17:45,012 --> 01:17:46,618
Sure.

2064
01:17:46,618 --> 01:17:48,494
- Is that okay?
- Oh, yes.

2065
01:17:48,494 --> 01:17:49,891
Let's go, let's go in.

2066
01:17:49,891 --> 01:17:51,830
[Owner: But... who are you?]

2067
01:17:51,830 --> 01:17:52,870
"Youn's Kitchen!"

2068
01:17:52,870 --> 01:17:54,863
[Youn's Kitchen? / Actress]

2069
01:17:54,863 --> 01:17:56,469
- Hello.
- Hello.

2070
01:17:56,469 --> 01:17:57,849
- Sit here.
- Yeah.

2071
01:17:57,849 --> 01:18:00,429
- Whoa!
- Hello.

2072
01:18:00,429 --> 01:18:01,800
What are you eating?

2073
01:18:01,800 --> 01:18:03,843
- What's good here?
- What's good here?

2074
01:18:03,843 --> 01:18:06,217
- Tteokbokki and sundae.
- Yeah.

2075
01:18:06,217 --> 01:18:08,170
They said the gukbap here is cheap...

2076
01:18:08,170 --> 01:18:09,809
The gukbap is really good.

2077
01:18:09,809 --> 01:18:12,267
- Do you come here often?
- Yes.

2078
01:18:13,034 --> 01:18:15,517
- Wow.
- Beef gukbap?

2079
01:18:15,517 --> 01:18:17,729
I guess we could eat a lot here.

2080
01:18:17,729 --> 01:18:20,096
Hey, didn't that fried squid
look really good earlier?

2081
01:18:20,096 --> 01:18:22,095
Yeah, everything looks good.

2082
01:18:23,441 --> 01:18:26,831
[Rising anticipation over the menu lineup]

2083
01:18:26,831 --> 01:18:28,955
Let's start with two beef gukbaps...

2084
01:18:28,955 --> 01:18:30,356
- Two?
- Yeah.

2085
01:18:30,356 --> 01:18:32,459
Two beef gukbaps,

2086
01:18:32,459 --> 01:18:33,899
and one fried dish.

2087
01:18:33,899 --> 01:18:36,171
- The sundae liver looks good.
- Ah, I want tteokbokki too... and sundae.

2088
01:18:36,171 --> 01:18:37,528
Let's just get the full set,
tteokbokki, fried dish, and sundae.

2089
01:18:37,528 --> 01:18:39,529
- That combo is 10,000 won.
- Oh.

2090
01:18:39,529 --> 01:18:41,109
- Then that's 20,000 total.
- And...

2091
01:18:41,109 --> 01:18:43,146
- How much do we have left?
- 11,000 won left.

2092
01:18:43,146 --> 01:18:44,778
- Then we should get some soju too.
- Let's get one.

2093
01:18:44,778 --> 01:18:46,831
Shall we just order that for now?

2094
01:18:48,049 --> 01:18:49,399
Excuse me.

2095
01:18:49,399 --> 01:18:52,625
Two beef gukbaps, one tteokbokki, fried dish,
a sundae combo, and one soju.

2096
01:18:52,625 --> 01:18:54,169
[Order complete]

2097
01:18:54,169 --> 01:18:56,206
It's really cheap though.

2098
01:18:56,206 --> 01:18:58,142
How did you even find this place?

2099
01:18:58,142 --> 01:18:59,928
- Well... we just searched online.
- We just searched online.

2100
01:18:59,928 --> 01:19:01,775
- So you just looked for cheap places?
- A good value...

2101
01:19:01,775 --> 01:19:03,068
- A good value spot.
- A good value spot?

2102
01:19:03,068 --> 01:19:05,705
Oh!

2103
01:19:05,705 --> 01:19:07,502
- Wow!
- Wow!

2104
01:19:07,502 --> 01:19:09,404
- Wow!
- But we're bad with spicy food.

2105
01:19:09,404 --> 01:19:10,971
- I'm not.
- Oh, really?

2106
01:19:10,971 --> 01:19:12,403
[Director Choi prepares insert shot]

2107
01:19:12,403 --> 01:19:16,624
- Wow!
- This plus the fried dish is 10,000 won.

2108
01:19:19,389 --> 01:19:20,582
- Let's eat.
- Try it!

2109
01:19:20,582 --> 01:19:21,685
- Thank you for the meal.
- Thank you for the meal.

2110
01:19:21,685 --> 01:19:23,465
Thank you for the meal.

2111
01:19:24,219 --> 01:19:25,592
It looks spicy.

2112
01:19:25,592 --> 01:19:26,817
[The "this is really good" frown
immediately appears]

2113
01:19:26,817 --> 01:19:28,623
Is it?

2114
01:19:28,623 --> 01:19:29,954
It's good!

2115
01:19:29,954 --> 01:19:32,248
Yum, it's delicious!

2116
01:19:32,248 --> 01:19:35,839
Wow, I was so hungry,
so I was even using my chopsticks like this.

2117
01:19:36,662 --> 01:19:38,755
[Jeez...]

2118
01:19:39,679 --> 01:19:43,935
[The fried dishes arrive shortly after]

2119
01:19:43,935 --> 01:19:46,546
[Immediately grabbing a piece]

2120
01:19:46,546 --> 01:19:49,069
[Dipping it deep into the tteokbokki sauce]

2121
01:19:49,069 --> 01:19:50,212
[Yum]

2122
01:19:52,082 --> 01:19:54,391
- Oh, this is good. The fried chili.
- Is it good?

2123
01:19:56,159 --> 01:19:57,489
Should we drink the soju now?

2124
01:19:57,489 --> 01:19:59,645
Do we have to go get it ourselves?

2125
01:19:59,645 --> 01:20:03,228
[The quick-to-act youngest immediately gets up]

2126
01:20:03,228 --> 01:20:04,762
Excuse me.

2127
01:20:04,762 --> 01:20:07,059
About the soju we ordered earlier...
should we just grab it ourselves?

2128
01:20:07,059 --> 01:20:09,416
Oh, I'll bring it right away...

2129
01:20:10,461 --> 01:20:12,005
Alright, let's drink Chamiseul.

2130
01:20:12,005 --> 01:20:14,366
[Daegu's local soju, "Chamiseul"]

2131
01:20:14,366 --> 01:20:18,139
"A fresh, clean morning,
with such wonderful people."

2132
01:20:18,139 --> 01:20:19,885
- That's totally about us.
- Right.

2133
01:20:19,885 --> 01:20:22,810
[Self-praise]

2134
01:20:23,662 --> 01:20:26,114
Two here, please.

2135
01:20:26,114 --> 01:20:29,408
[Gyeongsang-style beef gukbap
with a rich, spicy broth]

2136
01:20:29,408 --> 01:20:32,037
Wow, this is 5,000 won?

2137
01:20:32,037 --> 01:20:35,339
- Just a little over 5,000...
- Wow, this is 5,000 won. 5,000!

2138
01:20:35,339 --> 01:20:36,496
[Incredible value for money]

2139
01:20:36,496 --> 01:20:38,531
Yes, thank you!

2140
01:20:38,531 --> 01:20:42,009
- I haven't used this.
- Yeah, just give me a little, really.

2141
01:20:42,009 --> 01:20:43,619
- That's enough, that's enough.
- Is this enough?

2142
01:20:43,619 --> 01:20:44,742
I only want a little radish.

2143
01:20:44,742 --> 01:20:47,828
- I mistook that for radish.
- It's too much, really. That's enough.

2144
01:20:50,639 --> 01:20:52,594
Did you get some meat?

2145
01:20:54,315 --> 01:20:55,327
It's fine, it's fine.

2146
01:20:55,327 --> 01:20:57,303
[Aah, yum!]

2147
01:20:57,303 --> 01:21:00,219
[It is so good that it makes you
open the lid on your own...]

2148
01:21:00,219 --> 01:21:01,976
This is so good!

2149
01:21:01,976 --> 01:21:03,883
[Ladies first]

2150
01:21:03,883 --> 01:21:05,255
[No, you go first]

2151
01:21:05,255 --> 01:21:07,919
- You're 44, so you should go first.
- We're just having soju, why bring up age?

2152
01:21:07,919 --> 01:21:08,929
Po-po, you go first.

2153
01:21:08,929 --> 01:21:11,688
Don't say that.

2154
01:21:13,549 --> 01:21:15,275
It's hot.

2155
01:21:16,349 --> 01:21:18,333
For a safe...

2156
01:21:18,333 --> 01:21:20,496
and exciting journey.

2157
01:21:20,496 --> 01:21:22,843
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

2158
01:21:26,722 --> 01:21:28,422
Wow!

2159
01:21:30,356 --> 01:21:34,759
[Then everyone takes a spoonful of broth]

2160
01:21:34,759 --> 01:21:36,356
The underwear, and...

2161
01:21:36,356 --> 01:21:38,396
- Wow!
- And the toothbrush and all that...

2162
01:21:38,396 --> 01:21:40,181
- Oh, sir, we're just...
- No, it's okay, it's okay.

2163
01:21:40,181 --> 01:21:41,486
- We're just...
- It's okay, it's okay.

2164
01:21:41,486 --> 01:21:43,116
Oh, my...

2165
01:21:43,116 --> 01:21:47,104
[Simple, homey gimbap glistening with oil]

2166
01:21:47,104 --> 01:21:48,890
Thanks to PD Na Young Seok...

2167
01:21:48,890 --> 01:21:51,049
- Oh...
- Oh!

2168
01:21:51,049 --> 01:21:52,057
I'm not very familiar with...

2169
01:21:52,057 --> 01:21:53,183
- Wow.
- Wow...

2170
01:21:53,183 --> 01:21:54,706
younger people.

2171
01:21:54,706 --> 01:21:56,169
I watched "2 Days & 1 Night" a lot.

2172
01:21:56,169 --> 01:21:57,638
- Wow...
- Wow!

2173
01:21:57,638 --> 01:21:59,555
[Jealous...]

2174
01:21:59,555 --> 01:22:02,492
Just turn the camera that way.

2175
01:22:03,528 --> 01:22:04,896
Make it last.

2176
01:22:04,896 --> 01:22:06,102
- Wow...
- Wow!

2177
01:22:06,102 --> 01:22:07,536
- Thank you for the meal!
- Younger folks...

2178
01:22:07,536 --> 01:22:10,016
- I know you're big stars, but...
- Thank you!

2179
01:22:10,016 --> 01:22:11,582
- Thank you for the meal!
- Honestly, I don't really know.

2180
01:22:11,582 --> 01:22:12,822
[Production team: ha ha ha]

2181
01:22:12,822 --> 01:22:15,408
[Thanks to you, we get to enjoy this gimbap]

2182
01:22:15,408 --> 01:22:18,248
- Wow.
- Looks delicious!

2183
01:22:22,232 --> 01:22:24,282
- It's just plain gimbap, but it's good.
- Right.

2184
01:22:24,282 --> 01:22:26,309
- The rice is nice and sticky.
- Yeah.

2185
01:22:26,309 --> 01:22:27,402
Today...

2186
01:22:27,402 --> 01:22:30,113
we really picked the right place today.

2187
01:22:30,762 --> 01:22:32,883
[Hurry and eat up]

2188
01:22:32,883 --> 01:22:34,041
Go ahead, eat.

2189
01:22:34,041 --> 01:22:36,770
We're leaving right after we eat,
so hurry up and eat.

2190
01:22:36,770 --> 01:22:38,502
[Heart flutter]

2191
01:22:38,502 --> 01:22:39,938
We won't wait.

2192
01:22:39,938 --> 01:22:41,329
Can I just eat it?

2193
01:22:41,329 --> 01:22:43,341
[All staff put their cameras down]

2194
01:22:43,341 --> 01:22:46,231
[As if bound by fate,
they start eating together]

2195
01:22:46,231 --> 01:22:48,198
These days, something for 5,000 won...

2196
01:22:51,177 --> 01:22:53,469
Look at him.

2197
01:22:54,272 --> 01:22:57,721
[Fidgeting...]

2198
01:23:00,231 --> 01:23:03,398
[A real top star caught eating]

2199
01:23:04,389 --> 01:23:07,382
[Yum...]

2200
01:23:08,129 --> 01:23:11,808
[Since everyone's eating well, cheers]

2201
01:23:11,808 --> 01:23:13,610
It's really...

2202
01:23:14,339 --> 01:23:17,319
[A deep sigh from the core]

2203
01:23:18,052 --> 01:23:20,382
[A finishing sip of broth is a must]

2204
01:23:20,382 --> 01:23:21,468
This is good.

2205
01:23:21,468 --> 01:23:23,929
- Should we order just one more bottle?
- Let's get one more.

2206
01:23:23,929 --> 01:23:27,099
- Sir, we'll grab another bottle of soju.
- I'm curious what tomorrow's benefit will be.

2207
01:23:27,099 --> 01:23:28,770
- I'll get it for you.
- Okay.

2208
01:23:28,770 --> 01:23:30,305
[Now they're down to just 4,750 won]
Yeah.

2209
01:23:30,305 --> 01:23:32,219
Thank you. It's so delicious.

2210
01:23:32,219 --> 01:23:35,999
Tomorrow morning,
you'll get a fresh allowance anyway.

2211
01:23:35,999 --> 01:23:38,324
And there will probably be
your first benefit draw.

2212
01:23:38,324 --> 01:23:39,357
- In the morning?
- Yes.

2213
01:23:39,357 --> 01:23:41,690
- Oh.
- Not sure what it'll be, but in the morning...

2214
01:23:41,690 --> 01:23:44,299
- You're not going to take things away, right?
- No, nothing like that.

2215
01:23:44,299 --> 01:23:45,718
You'll be getting a new allowance,

2216
01:23:45,718 --> 01:23:48,676
so it'll just be added to what you have today.

2217
01:23:48,676 --> 01:23:51,486
Oh, I need to buy some underwear.

2218
01:23:51,486 --> 01:23:52,847
Seo Jun, how many did you bring?

2219
01:23:52,847 --> 01:23:54,499
I don't know, I need to check.

2220
01:23:54,499 --> 01:23:58,241
When I went to the US,
they had a washing machine there.

2221
01:23:58,241 --> 01:24:01,662
So I washed everything
and brought it back as is.

2222
01:24:01,662 --> 01:24:03,392
Oh, so they're not new, huh?

2223
01:24:03,392 --> 01:24:05,304
What, you expect brand new ones?

2224
01:24:06,859 --> 01:24:08,983
- What color are they?
- We'll buy you some tomorrow.

2225
01:24:08,983 --> 01:24:10,369
Various colors.

2226
01:24:10,369 --> 01:24:12,535
Honestly, yesterday...

2227
01:24:12,535 --> 01:24:15,015
- I got a perm yesterday.
- Right.

2228
01:24:15,015 --> 01:24:17,513
So the stylist told me, today and tomorrow...

2229
01:24:17,513 --> 01:24:20,624
- Not to wash your hair?
- She told me not to wash until I come back.

2230
01:24:20,624 --> 01:24:22,396
So I didn't shower.

2231
01:24:22,396 --> 01:24:23,931
Which means my underwear right now is...

2232
01:24:23,931 --> 01:24:24,942
[Shocking confession]

2233
01:24:24,942 --> 01:24:27,136
This is annoying...

2234
01:24:27,136 --> 01:24:28,929
[So ridiculous... can't help but laugh]
Until tomorrow...

2235
01:24:28,929 --> 01:24:32,068
- Until tomorrow...
- Hey, stop it!

2236
01:24:32,068 --> 01:24:34,709
That's a bit much for me.

2237
01:24:34,709 --> 01:24:37,263
[Same underwear since yesterday]
That's... because you didn't shower.

2238
01:24:37,263 --> 01:24:38,838
- Yeah.
- You didn't change?

2239
01:24:38,838 --> 01:24:40,563
Hey, you should change it!

2240
01:24:40,563 --> 01:24:42,784
- Why would I change if I didn't shower?
- That's...

2241
01:24:42,784 --> 01:24:45,459
that's totally different!

2242
01:24:45,459 --> 01:24:48,942
Anyway, the important thing is
I need a fresh pair right now.

2243
01:24:48,942 --> 01:24:51,645
Just wear his for today.

2244
01:24:51,645 --> 01:24:53,331
Just for today. Let's just buy it tomorrow...

2245
01:24:53,331 --> 01:24:54,969
- when we have money.
- Ugh, I don't want to hear this.

2246
01:24:54,969 --> 01:24:56,009
Do you have black ones?

2247
01:24:56,009 --> 01:24:58,545
Hey, how much are the ones
at convenience stores? That's...

2248
01:24:58,545 --> 01:25:00,660
I can't look it up right now, so I don't know.

2249
01:25:00,660 --> 01:25:03,277
- Stop by one on the way.
- Yeah, I'll check one.

2250
01:25:03,975 --> 01:25:05,381
How much do we have left?

2251
01:25:05,381 --> 01:25:08,445
- 4... 4,750 won.
- Nice!

2252
01:25:08,445 --> 01:25:10,460
- You handle it with this.
- Nice!

2253
01:25:10,460 --> 01:25:13,879
But what if the underwear costs
exactly 5,000 won?

2254
01:25:13,879 --> 01:25:15,947
Then I'll have to do a talent show right there.

2255
01:25:15,947 --> 01:25:17,088
[Underwear more precious than human dignity]

2256
01:25:17,088 --> 01:25:18,873
- You can't bargain there.
- Huh?

2257
01:25:18,873 --> 01:25:19,842
You can't haggle.

2258
01:25:19,842 --> 01:25:23,259
Then I'll just busk on the street,
what else can I do?

2259
01:25:23,259 --> 01:25:24,260
Shall we go?

2260
01:25:24,260 --> 01:25:26,019
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

2261
01:25:26,019 --> 01:25:28,466
- This is 3,500 won.
- You guys can have the rest.

2262
01:25:28,466 --> 01:25:31,102
- No, let's take it with us.
- Take it with us?

2263
01:25:31,102 --> 01:25:33,438
- They said to take it.
- This...

2264
01:25:33,438 --> 01:25:35,395
[Carefully saving the leftover soju]
Let's take it.

2265
01:25:36,581 --> 01:25:38,826
We'd like to pay, please.

2266
01:25:38,826 --> 01:25:41,385
- It's 88,000 won.
- What? No, just ours, please.

2267
01:25:41,385 --> 01:25:42,445
- Just the three of us.
- Oh, just this table?

2268
01:25:42,445 --> 01:25:45,139
- Yes.
- Oh, we can't pay for them.

2269
01:25:45,139 --> 01:25:46,180
Oh, dear.

2270
01:25:46,180 --> 01:25:48,536
- We were almost in trouble.
- Sorry.

2271
01:25:48,536 --> 01:25:50,376
- 27,000 won, yes that's right.
- 27,000 won, right.

2272
01:25:50,376 --> 01:25:52,524
- Yes, that's correct.
- Of course, it is.

2273
01:25:52,524 --> 01:25:54,459
Thank you!

2274
01:25:54,459 --> 01:25:56,245
Can we pack up the leftovers?

2275
01:25:56,245 --> 01:25:58,177
Hang on, I'll pack it so you can eat it later.

2276
01:25:58,177 --> 01:26:00,989
Just give us a plastic bag,
then we'll pack it ourselves.

2277
01:26:00,989 --> 01:26:03,546
- You never know, we might want it later.
- Alright.

2278
01:26:03,546 --> 01:26:05,308
- Let's go!
- Goodbye.

2279
01:26:05,308 --> 01:26:07,829
- Thank you!
- We enjoyed the meal!

2280
01:26:07,829 --> 01:26:09,239
Goodbye.

2281
01:26:09,239 --> 01:26:10,999
Was there a convenience store on the way?

2282
01:26:10,999 --> 01:26:12,048
If we go this way, I think there might be.

2283
01:26:12,048 --> 01:26:13,269
- Alright.
- Yeah, let's go this way.

2284
01:26:13,269 --> 01:26:15,902
Hey, there's a Thai massage place...

2285
01:26:15,902 --> 01:26:18,650
- go get a few from there.
- A few of what?

2286
01:26:18,650 --> 01:26:19,676
Oh, underwear?

2287
01:26:19,676 --> 01:26:22,103
- When you get a massage...
- You know, those clothes you change into.

2288
01:26:22,103 --> 01:26:24,438
[The journey has started
for Woo Shik's underwear]

2289
01:26:24,438 --> 01:26:25,648
Wait, what?

2290
01:26:25,648 --> 01:26:27,442
Excuse me, do you have underwear here?

2291
01:26:27,442 --> 01:26:29,279
No underwear?

2292
01:26:29,279 --> 01:26:31,181
Don't they sell underwear at saunas?

2293
01:26:31,181 --> 01:26:33,930
You don't sell men's underwear here, right?

2294
01:26:34,658 --> 01:26:35,923
Oh?

2295
01:26:35,923 --> 01:26:37,168
[They go anywhere for Woo Shik's underwear]

2296
01:26:37,168 --> 01:26:38,256
I feel like they would sell...

2297
01:26:38,256 --> 01:26:39,451
- But...
- Yeah.

2298
01:26:39,451 --> 01:26:42,381
But if it's like 7,000 won...
if we hadn't had that extra soju...

2299
01:26:42,381 --> 01:26:44,630
[Why is it that bad feelings are never wrong?]

2300
01:26:44,630 --> 01:26:46,563
Hey, I don't think this will work.

2301
01:26:46,563 --> 01:26:49,262
[The shocking price of underwear
leaves them speechless]

2302
01:26:49,262 --> 01:26:50,731
[XXXX won]

2303
01:26:50,731 --> 01:26:54,217
Come on, at least for underwear,
they should help us out a bit.

2304
01:26:54,217 --> 01:26:56,056
At this rate, I'm gonna get sick.

2305
01:26:56,056 --> 01:26:59,703
[The beginning of misfortune
caused by underwear, COMING SOON]

2306
01:26:59,703 --> 01:27:02,009
[Next week]

2307
01:27:02,009 --> 01:27:04,869
Now, there are benefits inside these pockets.

2308
01:27:04,869 --> 01:27:06,636
You'll draw them randomly.

2309
01:27:06,636 --> 01:27:08,376
- No way.
- Come on, no way.

2310
01:27:08,376 --> 01:27:10,763
[Only the most useful items,
carefully selected]

2311
01:27:10,763 --> 01:27:11,948
Oh...

2312
01:27:11,948 --> 01:27:13,829
I need this the most right now!

2313
01:27:13,829 --> 01:27:16,175
There are exactly three.
You can only choose one.

2314
01:27:16,175 --> 01:27:17,658
Please!

2315
01:27:17,658 --> 01:27:19,671
[Thrilling]

2316
01:27:19,671 --> 01:27:22,339
[What will be the result of
the first benefit draw?]

2317
01:27:22,339 --> 01:27:24,649
- Seo Jun, Yumi!
- Yes?

2318
01:27:24,649 --> 01:27:26,069
Where are we heading now?

2319
01:27:26,069 --> 01:27:27,368
- Namwon!
- Namwon!

2320
01:27:27,368 --> 01:27:28,872
Namwon!

2321
01:27:28,872 --> 01:27:30,274
- Oh, is this Ojakgyo Bridge?
- Yeah.

2322
01:27:30,274 --> 01:27:31,776
It looks really cute.

2323
01:27:31,776 --> 01:27:33,808
- Oh, I like it.
- Yeah, it's great.

2324
01:27:33,808 --> 01:27:35,378
Hey, places like this usually have great food.

2325
01:27:35,378 --> 01:27:37,519
- Hungry? Let's go!
- Let's go.

2326
01:27:37,519 --> 01:27:39,182
Shall we come back here tonight?

2327
01:27:39,182 --> 01:27:40,416
It's so delicious!

2328
01:27:40,416 --> 01:27:41,868
[Strangers who met by chance]

2329
01:27:41,868 --> 01:27:43,922
[Getting swept up in the music]

2330
01:27:43,922 --> 01:27:46,364
- Hey, there's a swing over there.
- What?

2331
01:27:46,364 --> 01:27:47,491
[Getting lost in childlike wonder]

2332
01:27:47,491 --> 01:27:48,522
Let's go!

2333
01:27:48,522 --> 01:27:51,495
[As they fully enjoy Namwon and have fun]

2334
01:27:51,495 --> 01:27:53,376
[Collapse]
Ugh...

2335
01:27:55,229 --> 01:27:57,139
Why is this so exhausting?

2336
01:27:57,139 --> 01:27:59,223
Is it because of our age?

2337
01:27:59,223 --> 01:28:01,258
[But there's still one big problem left]

2338
01:28:01,258 --> 01:28:04,583
- But I don't think there's any lodging.
- There aren't any...

2339
01:28:04,583 --> 01:28:05,931
- He picked up!
- Hey!

2340
01:28:05,931 --> 01:28:07,044
I'll ask quickly,

2341
01:28:07,044 --> 01:28:09,386
- can we rent your house in Namwon?
- Yeah.

2342
01:28:09,386 --> 01:28:10,583
- Address, address...
- Yeah, send me the address.

2343
01:28:10,583 --> 01:28:12,304
- Do we just go straight down now?
- Yeah.

2344
01:28:12,304 --> 01:28:13,317
Okay!

2345
01:28:13,317 --> 01:28:15,292
By the way, Seo Jun,
this is the right way, right?

2346
01:28:15,292 --> 01:28:17,227
Did we really walk this far earlier?

2347
01:28:17,227 --> 01:28:21,339
- Seo Jun, this is right, huh?
- Feels like we're going somewhere weird.

2348
01:28:21,339 --> 01:28:23,368
Why is the road like this?

2349
01:28:23,368 --> 01:28:24,806
Huh? What? This is a dead end.

2350
01:28:24,806 --> 01:28:26,886
[Will they be able to get to the house safely?]
